title: tortellini salad
directions: Dice peppers, onion, tomatoes and artichokes.
In a large bowl, mix vegetables, tortellini and Parmesan cheese.
Add Italian dressing.
Serves 4.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add all ingredients except noodles and mix well.
Cook noodles as directed.
Add to the rest of the ingredients.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of the casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered. Makes 2 casseroles.

title: pot roast pork
directions: Rub pork with salt and pepper.
Make tiny knife slits in the meat.
Insert garlic slivers in slits.
Broil meat 15 minutes to remove excess fat.
Place 1 sliced onion in the bottom of crock-pot.
Add pork roast and remaining ingredients to crock-pot. Cover and cook on high heat for 5 hours or on low 10 hours.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Spoon whipped topping evenly into 6 dessert dishes using a spoon.
Spread into bottom and up sides of each dish.

title: barbecued roast beef sandwiches
directions: Make Zesty Barbecue Sauce. Stir beef into sauce. Cover and simmer about 5 minutes or until beef is
hot. Fill buns with beef mixture.

title: radican's seafood shrimp mold
directions: Soak gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat soup to boil.
Add gelatine to soup and cool.
Cream together cream cheese and mayonnaise; mix into gelatine.
Add chopped vegetables.
Place in a 2-quart mold and refrigerate until jelled.
Serve with crackers.

title: blackened fish
directions: Dust the fillets with flour.
Heat the butter and oil in large, heavy pan over medium heat.
Add fillets and cook 3 minutes on one side; turn and sprinkle seasonings evenly over the browned side.
Cook another 3 minutes and turn, sprinkling this side with seasonings.
Turn the heat on high and sear each side for about 2 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine; blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
When thickened, stir in chicken and vegetables.
Pour into Jiffy pie crust bottom and cover with top crust.
Cut slits to allow steam to escape.
Cook, uncovered, at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes (until crust is brown).

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat
oven

In medium mixing bowl combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend in
milk,
melted butter and vanilla extract; beat until smooth. Pour batter into square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches) or (9 x 9
x 2-inches).
In small bowl combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle mixture evenly over
batter.
Pour
hot
water
over top; do not stir. Bake
40 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand 15 minutes; spoon
into dessert
dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top. Garnish as desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: never-fail pie meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and salt in saucepan; cook until thick and clear. Cool slightly. Beat egg whites with electric mixer until frothy. Continue beating while pouring in cornstarch mixture. Beat 5 minutes. Use meringue to cover cooled filling in pie shell, sealing edges to crust. Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes or until meringue is golden. Makes 1 pie.

title: cathy's kraut
directions: Can be topped with sausage pieces. Bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: vegetable oil biscuits
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients;
stir in oil and milk at the same time.
Roll
out dough between sheets of waxed paper on a dampened surface.
Cut rolled out dough with a floured biscuit cutter or cut
into squares with a knife.
Bake at 450° on an ungreased pan for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: pumpkin swirl
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan or bread pan. Line with greased wax paper. Set aside. Beat eggs at high speed with an electric mixer until thick and pale. Gradually add sugar, beating until soft peaks form and sugar dissolves, 2 to 4 minutes. Fold in pumpkin. Combine biscuit mix and spices; fold into pumpkin mixture and spread evenly into prepared pan. Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes. Sift the powdered sugar onto a 15 x 10 dishtowel. When the cake is done, immediately loosen from sides of pan and turn out onto sugared towel. Carefully peel off wax paper. Starting at narrow end, roll up cake and towel together and cool completely on a wire rack, seam side down. Beat cream cheese and butter at medium speed with mixer until creamy. Add powdered sugar and vanilla, beating well. Unroll cake; spread with cream cheese mixture and re-roll without towel. Place on a serving plate, seam side down. Ice the top with cream cheese mixture and sprinkle with pecans.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent. Combine onion, rice and hot broth. Bring to a boil on top of range. Cover and place in a 325° oven for 20 minutes. Serve and listen to the compliments!

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop hearts in food processor.
Mix with mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, Worcestershire sauce and red pepper; mix.
Put in a baking dish and sprinkle more cheese on top before baking.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Serve hot on Ritz crackers.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: In large saucepan combine cream cheese, parmesan, butter and milk, stirring constantly until smooth.
Toss pasta lightly with sauce, coating well.
Leftovers freeze well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage-cheese puffs
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Melt butter in scalded milk.
Add eggs.
Layer oysters and crackers in a 2-quart bowl.
Pour milk and egg mixture over salt and pepper to taste.
Uncover for 1 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and 2/3 of the sesame seed in bowl.
Add mixture of mayonnaise and curry powder; toss to mix. Sprinkle with remaining sesame seed.
May put on lettuce leaf.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding with mixer until thickened.
Add coconut and nuts and fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Chill at least 2 or 3 hours.

title: din din chili
directions: Heat the oil in a pot; cook the meat until it turns brown. Add everything to the pot except the kidney beans.
Stir well. Don't let stick.
Let it simmer for about 40 minutes.
Add the beans, water and all, if pot will hold it.
Simmer 20 more minutes.
Get 5 bowls ready and enjoy.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Make sure you can not shake pie in middle, it is done.

title: nestle cake
directions: Mix sifted flour, sugar and salt together.
Set aside.
In pot on the stove, mix margarine, water and chocolate and bring to boil.
Pour over flour mixture; stir by hand until thoroughly blended.
Add 2 eggs and buttermilk in which you have put vanilla and soda.
Thoroughly mix and pour into a sheet cake pan, approximately 11 x 14-inch (greased).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Make icing and pour over hot cake.

title: fluffy pink stuff
directions: Mix lemon juice with
Eagle Brand milk.
Add cherry pie filling, pineapple, sour cream and nuts and fold in Cool Whip. Mix well and chill.
Will serve 12 to 15 people.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, oil and zucchini.
Add flour and mix well.
Batter should be of cake-like consistency.
Divide batter evenly between three 9 x 5-inch bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie(one large pie)
directions: Cream sugar, butter and flour.
Beat eggs and add to mixture. Add milk and nuts.
Pour into 1 large ready made or homemade pie shell.
Bake at 375° until done, top is brown and knife comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: lemon glow angel cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions.
Cover with wax paper; cool.
Cut a 1-inch slice from top of cake; set aside.
Cut around 1 inch from hole in cake and 1 inch from outside of cake. Lift out to make a well in cake, leaving a 1-inch base.
Beat pudding smooth.
Fold half into lemon pie filling; set aside half of lemon mixture.
Spoon remaining into cake.
Replace top of cake. Prepare topping mix.
Fold in remaining pudding.
Frost top and sides of cake.
Chill before serving.
Spoon remaining pudding mixture over top of cake.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done; drain grease.
Add onion, green pepper and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
In bowl, mix eggs and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Add sausage mixture to eggs.
Pour into pie shell and top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Using a shaker, sprinkle turkey inside and out with salt and pepper.
Pour enough oil into a 40-quart pot so turkey will be covered when lowered into pot.
Make sure pot is large enough so oil won't overflow.
Heat oil to 350° to 375°.
Tie a heavy string to legs and slowly lower turkey into pot.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes per pound.
A 15 pound bird will be done in 50 or 60 minutes.
Test for doneness at thigh joint.
Carefully remove turkey and drain upright on legs so all oil will drain from cavity.
Carve as usual.

title: fajita fish
directions: Combine marinade with other ingredients and beat.
Preheat skillet at medium-high heat.
Place fish and marinade in skillet. Saute about 5 minutes (or according to your desire).

title: marinated round steak
directions: Saute garlic in canola oil 2 minutes; add tarragon, tomatoes and sherry and cook for 10 minutes on medium heat.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over steak and marinate 3 to 6 hours, turning once in a while.
Barbecue as usual, basting with sauce freely.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place fryer in a baking dish. Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken. Spoon mushroom soup over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemony green beans
directions: Wash green beans.
Trim ends.
Remove strings.
Drop beans into a large saucepan of boiling water.
Cook 7 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain well.
Combine the beans and tomatoes in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine lemon juice and the next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Pour over vegetables, tossing gently to coat.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken and cut in pieces.
Add to Stove Top stuffing. Pour melted oleo over Stove Top stuffing.
Mix and add water chestnuts, celery, green pepper and dried parsley.
Mix soup, mayonnaise (not Miracle Whip) and sour cream and add to stuffing mixture.
Pour all in pan.
I sometimes use 2 small pans.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Wash eggplant; do not peel.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roll in bread crumbs; dip in eggs and then again in bread crumbs. Depending upon the size of eggplant, more bread crumbs and eggs may be necessary.
Place in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Heat about 1/8-inch oil in skillet.
Fry eggplant slices until tender and golden brown on both sides.
Add more oil if necessary.
Drain. Line a shallow 2-quart baking dish with sauce.
Add a layer of Mozzarella slices, more sauce and a sprinkling of basil and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers until dish is full.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick beer wheat bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix, flour and sugar.
Add eggs and beer. Beat about 1 minute or until well blended.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture, alternating with sour cream and ending with dry ingredients.
Add flavor.
Generously grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Cover bottom of pan with nuts.
Spoon batter over nuts. Sprinkle with nutmeg or mace.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove from oven and remove from pan immediately.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and brush with melted oleo.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with onion. Mix soups and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: glennda's baked potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with peeling on.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Salt to taste.
Fry bacon crisp; break into pieces.
Dice onions; add bacon and onions to potatoes.
Heat cheese and mayonnaise until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour cheese mixture over potato mixture.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions firm, drain and wash in colander.
Pour into bowl; add rest of ingredients.
Add more mayonnaise, if desired, so it's not dry.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salt water 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing mix in bottom of baking dish.
Add squash mixture.
Spoon remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel crunch apple pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine caramels and water, cooking and stirring over low heat until smooth.
In a pastry shell, layer apples and caramel sauce.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples and caramel sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until apples are tender.
Cool.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 375° for about 1 hour or until soft.
Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato.
Scoop out the pulp and put into a bowl.
Separate eggs; add yolks to the potato pulp.
Blend until smooth.
Add butter and cream.
Season with salt and pepper. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into potato mixture.
Fill shells with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven at 375° for about 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: papoose pie
directions: Blend flour and butter together.
Pat into the bottom of a pie pan.
Press the pecans into the pie crust.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.
Set pie crust aside to cool.
Then cream together the powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread this into the cooled crust.
Slice the bananas and place on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Cover with the Cool Whip.
Spoon the cherry pie filling on top of the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until it is served.

title: roast corn
directions: Melt butter with chives and parsley.
Brush corn with butter mixture, salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Place these ingredients in a small bowl; let stand about 15 minutes.
Add enough plain sifted flour to make a stiff dough. Place in a greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Work down with hands and make into rolls.
Let rolls rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush lightly with margarine.
Bake in a hot oven (450°) until brown, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: shipwreck
directions: Grease large casserole dish or roasting pan.
Layer ingredients in the order they are listed.
If tomatoes don't have much liquid, add some water to keep casserole moist.
Bake at 325 ° for 1 hour, covered.
Then 10 to 15 minutes uncovered if ground beef not browned.

title: chapatti
directions: Mix; break off small portions and roll in balls.
Roll balls out flat and thin; cook in oiled hot skillet or on griddle.
These are done when brown spots appear.
Cook both sides.
Eat plain or with butter or honey.
Makes 5 to 6 Chapatti.

title: pueblo beans
directions: Wash beans. Put in a 6-quart kettle with 3 quarts water and simmer for about 4 hours. Mix remaining ingredients with beans and water. Place in a 4-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours. Add more water if necessary. Yields about 10 servings.

title: frozen citrus pie
directions: Beat concentrate in large mixer bowl, about 30 seconds.
Blend in ice cream.
Fold in whipped topping until smooth.
Freeze if necessary until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.
Store leftover pie in freezer.
Especially good in summer months.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Slice roast into small pieces 1/4-inch thick.
Cook roast in pressure cooker for 25 minutes; add vegetables to roast.
Cook until done.
Add tomato juice and salt and pepper to taste.

title: nancy's boiled fish
directions: Preheat broiler.
Rinse steaks or fillets; pat dry with paper towels.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons mayonnaise over top of each steak or fillet.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 teaspoons cheese on top of each.
Place on broiling pan. Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat, 5 to 8 minutes or until top is puffed and brown and fish tests done.
Serves 4.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Melt butter, add chopped onion and cook until tender.
Add paprika, pepper, sugar, mustard, sauce, catsup and vinegar.
With sharp knife cut a 3 inch slit in each frankfurter.
Place frankfurters in a flat baking pan, slit side up.
Pour sauce over all and bake in a moderate oven 350° for 20 minutes basting frequently.
Place frankfurters in split, toasted, buttered buns. Serve extra sauce separately.

title: eagle brand chocolate icing
directions: Melt the chocolate squares in the Eagle Brand. Add the cold water, vanilla and pinch of salt. Use small pan. Stir constantly until mixture thickens and becomes shiny. Pour immediately over cake.

title: sunset cherry pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer, mixing until well blended.
Stir in 1 cup pie filling and 1/4 cup pineapple.
Fold whipped topping into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Top with remaining pie filling and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin ice cream squares
directions: Mix crumbs with butter and sugar.
Press into the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Combine pumpkin with sugar, salt and spices. Fold in ice cream.
Pour into crumb-lined pan.
Cover.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares about 20 minutes before serving. Top with whipped cream and pecans.
Makes 9 (3-inch) squares.

title: mom's one-bowl white cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar,
baking
powder
and salt into bowl. Drop in Crisco.
Add about 2/3 cup milk, then vanilla and beat until smooth.
Add
egg whites; mix thoroughly.
Add remaining milk and beat until well
blended.
Pour
batter
into 2 (8 or 9-inch) pans which have
been
greased
and
floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use desired frosting.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: barbecue muffins
directions: Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Flatten into 5-inch circles. Press each into the bottom and up sides of a greased muffin pan; set aside.

title: pizza crust
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Add yeast to warm water and dissolve. Mix in the flour and salt.
Knead for about 5 minutes, adding more flour only if necessary.
Cover and let rise for 1/2 hour.
Roll or pull by hand.
Place on greased pizza pan.
Makes 2 to 3 crusts.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: california flank steak
directions: Rub liberal amounts brown sugar into both sides of the flank steak.
Don't be stingy!
Lay the steak into an oblong container and cover with soy sauce.
Remember to lift the steak so the sauce gets underneath.
Cover and marinate for 1 hour.
Turn the steak over, re-cover and marinate for 1 hour more.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Mix liquid ingredients with melted butter and bouillon.
Add olives, mushrooms and (last) the rice.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Place the chicken pieces in a large saucepan and cover them with the water.
Add the celery, bay leaf, onion, salt and peppercorns.
Place the pan over high heat and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to low, cover the pan and simmer for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder and spices.
Fold in flour mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured (or Pam sprayed) jelly roll pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on a soft towel, loosen cake and invert onto towel.
Roll up cake in towel.
Cool cake completely.
Unroll and spread with filling.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a pastry shell and bake on lower shelf in a moderate oven (375°) 40 to 45 minutes.
This makes one large pie.

title: joyce's seven layer salad
directions: Combine lettuce, broccoli, cauliflower, onion and cucumber with mayonnaise.
Blend well, making sure everything is covered with mayonnaise.
Pour bottle of Italian dressing over mixture and garnish with tomatoes and shredded cheese.

title: chocolate chip nut cake
directions: Mix together, except chocolate chips and nuts, and beat 5 to 10 minutes.
In another bowl, mix chocolate chips and nuts.

title: turtle cake
directions: Remove paper from caramels.
Follow instructions on cake mix box to mix.
Pour half of batter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake this half for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: penne with tomato cream sauce
directions: Brown sausage meat; put aside.
In a heavy saucepan, combine the tomatoes with juice, cream, garlic and tarragon; bring the liquid to a boil, breaking up the tomatoes.
Add sausage; simmer mixture for 25 to 30 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Cook penne 12 to 15 minutes in boiling water; drain well.
Toss with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Drain pineapple (keep juice).
Beat sugar, eggs and butter until light and fluffy.
Pour over bread cubes and drained pineapple.
Add enough juice to moisten well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve from oven.

title: aunt bea's potatoes
directions: In skillet, saute onions in oil or margarine.
Combine with hash browns, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Spread in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cornflakes and melted butter. Sprinkle over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pie crust biscuits
directions: Using medium size mixing bowl, mix together pie crust mix, baking powder and baking soda.
Make a well in the center and add buttermilk all at once.
Stir only until dough clings together.

title: good corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: In heavy saucepan, stir grits slowly into boiling water.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Allow grits to cool.
Mix well with beaten eggs.
In greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish, alternate layers of grits and cheese.
Pour milk over top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ralph's cream-style corn
directions: Open can; empty into pot.
Heat on medium-high to desired warmth.
Serves 1 to 2 people per can.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until it falls off bone.
Reserve 4 cups broth. Take chicken off bone.
Combine broth, chicken and all other ingredients in large pan.
Cook over low heat until spaghetti absorbs most of liquid.
(If you want more spaghetti, cook it first, then add remaining ingredients.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
Mash bananas. Beat eggs until light.
Mix bananas and eggs together.
Add dry mixture and mix. Add nuts and stir well.
Put in a 9 x 5-inch buttered loaf pan. Some like to add 2 tablespoons melted butter to the batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, vanilla and water until foamy.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat until slightly stiff.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually, then fold in flour and sugar mixture gradually.
Bake at 375°.

title: amanda's picante salsa
directions: Dip tomatoes in boiling water to remove skins.
Chop all vegetables and put in large pot or dishpan.
(I use food processor for peppers.)
Cook on medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes or until starts to thicken.
Dissolve 3 tablespoons cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Add to salsa; cook a few minutes longer to thicken.
Put in hot jars to seal.
Makes about 14 pints.

title: mom's cobbler
directions: Place fruit in pie dish.
Mix sugar and Bisquick.
Pour over fruit.
Slice margarine over sugar mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until well browned.

title: bean salad
directions: Wash beans in cold water and drain.
Mix beans, bell pepper and onions.
Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, pepper and salt.
Pour over beans and toss lightly until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onions and olives.
Spread thin layer of mixture on tortilla.
Arrange four slices of ham over cheese.
Tightly roll up tortilla.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator at least 3 hours or overnight.
To serve, cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Makes about 64 appetillas.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Place vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Salt and pepper meat.
Place into pot.
Add liquid and cover.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours).
Remove meat and vegetables with spoon.
Thicken remaining liquid for gravy if desired.

title: peanut butter cup pie(lite choices)
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Press crust ingredients into a 9-inch pie plate; chill.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain off excess fat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Serve with spaghetti noodles.

title: marshmallow puffs
directions: Line a 9-inch pan with foil; butter the foil.
Arrange marshmallows in pan.
In a double boiler or microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over marshmallows.
Chill completely.
Cut between marshmallows. Yields 3 dozen.
White chocolate chips can be substituted.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in lemonade.
Add cold water and cranberry juice.
Pour over ice in punch bowl; slowly pour in 28 ounce bottle of ginger ale.
Chill.
Yield:
12 cups.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, and taco mix.
Spread on 8 inch pie plate.
Layer refried beans, then salsa.
Top with cheese, lettuce and olives.
Refrigerate up to 1 hour then serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and let set overnight or several hours in refrigerator.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: curried chicken breasts
directions: Conventional Oven:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together gravy mix, curry powder and water.
Place in large size brown-in-bag. Place in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in single layer in the bag.
Cut slits in the bag and bake for 45 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Add enough water to hold ingredients together, sprinkling evenly and mixing with fork to form ball.
Makes enough for 8-inch or 9-inch pie, either 2-crust or bottom crust and crisscross strips on top.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small serving bowl and set aside for the flavors to meld, about 3 hours or overnight is best. Keeps about 1 week. Good on almost everything.
Makes about 2 cups of salsa.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening
and
sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Alternate
adding flour and cream (divide into thirds).
Cook at 300°
at
least 2 hours or until brown. Start in a cold oven!
"Makes a crusty, delicious cake."

title: indian fry bread
directions: In a bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Slowly add cold water, a little at a time, until dough forms.
Divide into balls about the size of a softball.
On a floured surface, roll balls out into an even circle about 1/4-inch thick.
In a large frying pan, heat lard or oil on medium heat.
Oil should be about 1-inch deep. Place fry bread in pan.
Flip with tongs. When lightly brown on both sides, remove and place on paper towels.
Serve as a meal with beans, cheese or add lettuce, tomatoes to make a Navajo taco. Serve as dessert with sprinkled powdered sugar.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in buttered baking pan; place sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.
Serve sprinkled with chopped parsley.
Serve over white rice.

title: soup for a winter evening
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: easy festive fudge(chocolate or peanut butter or butterscotch)
directions: Mix in a heavy 2-quart pan the sugar, milk, marshmallows, margarine and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil (bubbling all over the top).
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; mix 3 minutes. Meanwhile, butter a 10-inch pan and dust with flour. Pour mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise and pour over broccoli and cauliflower.
Chill before serving.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring water to boil; add rice.
Boil for 14 minutes.
Drain rice (optional).
Mix remaining ingredients while boiling.
Cook until thick; stir constantly.
Serve warm or cold with cinnamon sugar.
Can be rewarmed in microwave.
Use 2-quart kettle or larger.

title: baklava
directions: Grind nuts and combine with cinnamon and sugar in a large bowl.
Melt butter. Brush bottom of a 14 x 20-inch pan with butter.
Place one pastry sheet and brush with butter, repeating process until 6 pastry sheets line pan.

Add nut mixture. Add another sheet. Brush with butter and sprinkle with nut mixture. Repeat process until all ingredients are used, ending with 4 layers of buttered filo on top. Cut into diamond shapes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber delight
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix sour cream, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Mix lightly.
Let stand one hour before serving.
Serves 6.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients and let set overnight.
Serve with king size chips.

title: wild duck
directions: Brown dressed ducks in butter.
Remove duck and make water, flour, salt and pepper gravy from butter.
Add wine to gravy. Place ducks in roaster, breast down.
Cover with gravy.
Cover roaster and cook in very slow oven at 200° for at least 4 hours. Check often and add more water, wine and seasonings if necessary. Serve with wild rice.

title: company chicken
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add rice; lay chicken in rice.
Sprinkle soup mix over all.
Pour 2 cups water.
Spread can of soup over chicken; add can of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tahini sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend well.
Use as sauce for fish or make beef/lamb/onion and parsley patties and use as sauce for them.

title: monkey bread
directions: Butter a tube pan.
Cut each biscuit in half and roll into a ball.
Place 1/2 of them in pan.
Bring rest of ingredients (except nuts) to a boil.
Add nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over biscuits that are in the tube pan.
Put remaining biscuits on top of first layer.
Top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Put in heavy skillet over heat until water evaporates and sugar crystallizes.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Let it cool.
Enjoy!

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook about 1 minute.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir 1 minute.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
(Drain mandarins and discard juice.)
Refrigerate.

title: apple butter
directions: Use apple pulp left from preparing apple juice for jelly. Press through food mill.
Measure pulp.
Add sugar and spices; cook until the flavors are blended well, about 15 minutes.
To prevent sticking, stir frequently as mixture thickens.
(If too thick, add a small amount of water for desired consistency.) Makes 5 pints.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Melt margarine and add to brown sugar.
Mix well and let cool slightly. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake in large 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 3/4-inch greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except stuffing mix and butter.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Toss stuffing mix with butter and spoon over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: primavera vegetables with linguine
directions: In large skillet heat oil.
Saute onion and garlic for 1 minute.
Add zucchini, yellow squash and bell pepper.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in reserved tomato juice, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes and basil and simmer 1 minute.

title: beat 'n eat frosting
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in small deep bowl.
Add boiling water. Beat to stiff peaks with eggbeater or electric beater.
Spread between layers and on top and sides of 8-inch cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: rice krispies candy
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter in microwave.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Yields approximately 7 dozen.
This is a holiday requirement at my house.

title: ham casserole
directions: Simmer butter, onion, pepper and red pepper; mix together soup, corn and Ro-Tel.
Put ham, potatoes and spaghetti in casserole dish.
Then pour over soup.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Then put Velveeta cheese on top.
Put in oven for 5 minutes.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Drain liquid off grape leaves.
Put leaves in 3-quart pan of cold water.
Heat to boiling; drain.

title: hawaiian dessert(diabetic recipe)
directions: Bring juice to a boil; add gelatin, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Combine pineapple and milk in blender; blend well. Add gelatin mixture, almond extract and ice.
Mix thoroughly in blender.
Pour into dessert dishes.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: d.p. whitmer's blueberry muffins(this recipe won third place in "connecticut post" contest.)
directions: Lightly spray the inside of muffin tins with nonstick spray. With a paper towel or tissue, gently wipe the spray inside each muffin cup.
Spread soft butter around inside of each muffin cup liberally.
Set aside tins in cool place.
Into a bowl, put 1/3 cup flour, 1/3 cup confectioners sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; mix well, then add the fresh or hard frozen berries and mix well. Reserve at room temperature.

title: red salt
directions: Excellent on all meats.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Prepare strawberry Jell-O as on package, omitting 2 cups of cold water.
Mix in strawberries.
Place torn angel food cake in 9 x 13-inch pan and pour strawberries over cake.
Let sit until firm and spread Cool Whip over strawberries.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: dry mustard pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in a crock, except cucumbers.
Wash cucumbers and add as they are available.
Put plate over cucumbers in crock.
Put large rock on plate to hold cucumbers under mixture until cucumbers lighten up.
They are then ready to eat.

title: low-fat oven fried catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 400° to 450° or adjust oven if it cooks fast. Dip fish in egg whites, then coat in meal.
Arrange in pan lined with aluminum foil and sprayed with Pam.
Place in oven; turn once.
Place under broiler if you want fish crunchy and browned. Bake 7 to 8 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix sweet potatoes with sugar, milk, salt and orange rind. Scoop up about 1/4 cup potato mixture and shape into a ball around a marshmallow, using more, if needed, to cover.
Roll in corn flakes (or pecans).
Place on baking dish sprayed with Pam and freeze, covered.

title: champagne cake
directions: Combine cake mix, club soda, pudding mix, eggs and oil.
Beat with mixer.
Stir in (by spoon) the cherries, nuts and pineapple. Make three layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: fun castle
directions: Wash pieces
of
brick	and
rocks in plain water until they are thoroughly
wet.
Wet sponge and wring it out.	Place rocks, bricks and/or
sponge
in
a shallow glass bowl (do not use metal of	any
kind).
Arrange to suit your fancy, placing on top of each
other
to get the desired shape you want.
The good thing about the
sponge is that you can cut it to desired shapes.
Mix water,
bluing
(you
can
still
get this at the grocery store, I just
called
to see) and ammonia in a glass jar.	Pour over
the rocks,
being sure to dampen all of them with the mixture.
Put a
drop or two of food color and a few drops of bluing on
one
or two of the rocks.
Sprinkle with 4 tablespoons salt
and
watch it grow.
Add 2 tablespoons each water and ammonia	after
two days
to edge of bowl.
This is straight from Heloise!

title: marinated carrots
directions: Layer carrots, onion and bell pepper.
Boil remaining ingredients and pour over layered carrots, onion and bell pepper. Refrigerate until chilled or overnight.
Lasts several days in refrigerator.

title: world's easiest fudge
directions: Spray an 8 x 8 or 9 x 9 microwavable dish with nonstick spray. Place chocolate chips and Eagle Brand milk in dish.
Stir. Microwave approximately 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir.
If using nuts, add those in.
Microwave at 30 second intervals until chocolate chips are completely melted.
Refrigerate.
Takes approximately 4 to 6 hours to set up.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onion, celery and broccoli in butter for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth.
Place rice in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over; do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: coney sauce
directions: Fry together.
Drain hamburger and onions.
Mix together in a large kettle sugar, vinegar, juice, tomato puree, chili powder, pepper, catsup, sauce, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Add hamburger and onion to this mix.
Salt to taste.
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Cool; run it through a meat grinder.
One pint makes 8 or 9 Coneys.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and mix well. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, milk, sour cream, chilies, jalapeno and 1/4 teaspoon cumin in blender.
Mix cream cheese, onion, chicken and 1/4 teaspoon cumin in large bowl.
Roll mixture in flour tortillas. Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan and pour liquid mixture over top. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes, then uncovered for 5 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Put all 3 cans of soup in large deep baking dish;
pour in cup of rice and stir together.
Lay chicken pieces on
top;
cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: boo's spicy salsa
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients in blender. Add the bell pepper. Mix all ingredients and cook for 1 1/2 hours or desired thickness. Then can.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Lightly grease to large baking sheets with butter or vegetable shortening.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger, and nutmeg.
Using a pastry blender or two forks, work the margarine into flour mixture until
thoroughly mixed.
Mix the chopped walnuts with the oatmeal.
Stir into flour mixture.
Beat in egg and bananas.
Mix well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of batter onto baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 12 - 15 minutes, or until the cookies have browned around the edges.
Remove from oven.
Cool cookies for 2 - 3 minutes and transfer to wire racks to cool completely.

title: walnut roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the last 3 and bake in an oiled meat loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix as directed.
Prepare pie filling, reducing milk to 2 cups.
Blend in half whipped topping.
Arrange banana in shell and put pudding mixture in shell.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: candied walnuts
directions: Bake walnuts for 15 minutes at 375°.
Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and salt in saucepan; cook over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Do not stir.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts. Stir until mixture becomes creamy and sticks to the nuts.
Dump on cookie sheet and spread as it cools.

title: pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Mix and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish; bake at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Let cool.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl blend all ingredients on low setting, then beat 2 to 3 minutes on medium.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Cool.

title: georgia special
directions: Mix well and cook at 350° until done. Cool.

title: fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low to medium heat until mixture reaches 240 degrees on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Beat until fudge starts to thicken and turns dull.
Pour into buttered pie pan.

title: punch for 25
directions: Make gelatin as directed on package.
Add rest of ingredients except ginger ale and mix thoroughly.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Sherbet may also be added when ready to serve.

title: stackups grande
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Stir in Cheez Whiz and chili powder.
Layer tortillas and meat mixture in two stacks in 13 1/2 x 8 3/4-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with tomato; cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in a small bowl until smooth.
Set aside.
Drain pineapple and mix in large bowl with banana pieces, strawberries, nuts and whipped cream.
This should be well mixed. Add cream cheese/sugar mixture and mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 11-inch pan and freeze for 3 hours before serving.
This can be stored in the freezer for at least 3 weeks and can be used as either a salad or dessert.

title: "grumbire" soup(hearty and filling on cold winter days.)
directions: First:
Cover potatoes and onion with water and cook until soft.
Add milk and heat through, stirring gently.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pork and pea pods
directions: Mix soy sauce, cooking sherry, garlic and ginger for a marinade.
Add meat, tossing to coat evenly.
Cover tightly. Refrigerate at least four hours or longer.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine sugar, water and instant coffee granules.
Simmer slowly for 40 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Add vodka. Pour into clean, empty bottles.
Let set at least 3 weeks.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix sour cream and brown sugar together and let set overnight in refrigerator.
In the morning, add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes one regular bread pan loaf.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meats, garlic and salt, add next 5 ingred. Then add 1 tsp each of chili powder, thyme, tarragon, basil, marjorum, oregano, celery salt, 1-2 bay leaves, sugar to taste, seasoning salt romano or parmesan. Simmer for 2-3 hrs.

title: whole-wheat apple cinnamon muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Peel the apple and grate it into another bowl.
Stir in the yogurt and the sugar until the sugar dissolves.
Stir in the egg, molasses, oil and 1/4 cup water.
Stir the flour mixture into the yogurt mixture until just combined.
The muffin batter will be lumpy.
Spoon into prepared muffin pans.
Bake at 400° until edges start to brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Make ahead and freeze.
Great for breakfast.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken and rice)
directions: Mix salt, garlic and oregano; rub chicken inside and out. Saute tomatoes, peppers and onion; add chicken and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add achote coloring, rice, olives and capers; mix well. Add liquid; stir and cover.
Cook until the rice is done and all water has been absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Garnish with strips of pimentos and peas.

title: carolyn craig's mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix well and drop in greased muffin tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Mix and spread real thin on buttered cookie sheet (press and spread with palms of hands).
Brush top with slightly beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.
Cook in 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in sticks 1 x 3-inches while hot and cool in pan.

title: whipped pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Using electric mixer, mix sugar, margarine, Crisco and eggs; mix very well.
Be sure to use whipped margarine; it's the secret to the cake because no baking powder or soda is used.
Add flour and milk, then flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in flavoring by hand.

title: chicken enchiladas(low-fat)
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with vegetables
directions: Tear off 2 (12 x 18-inch) sheets of aluminum foil and rub them lightly with oil.
Place onion slices on each sheet.
Flatten breasts to 1/4-inch thick and place over onions.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread over each chicken breast.
Top with carrots, zucchini and mushrooms.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with basil, garlic powder and paprika.
Seal edges tightly to make package.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs and cream.
Stir in cheese and sausage.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Puree chilies in blender.
Saute in 2 tablespoons oil (use a 2-quart Dutch oven), onion, pureed chilies and garlic.

Puree stewed tomatoes in blender and add to the sauteed mixture along with beef broth, cream of chicken soup, chicken broth, salt, sugar, lemon pepper, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, cumin and Tabasco.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: hamburger and sausage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° until rice is tender.

title: chicken & dumplings
directions: Mix dough.
Roll out to about the same thickness as pie crust, prick dough with fork & cut into 2 inch wide strips then break into pieces about 2 inches long.
Add enough water to broth to make about 2 qts.
Bring broth to boil, add chicken & dumplings & salt & pepper to taste.
This makes enough to serve 8-10 people.

title: seasoned pork roast
directions: Combine garlic salt and pepper. Rub over roast. Place roast on rack in roasting pan and roast in a 350° oven for 40 minutes per pound.

title: fruity banana milk
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender or jar.
Cover and blend or shake until mixed well.
Makes 3 servings.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk in a medium sauce pan; boil 3 minutes.
Stir in cocoa, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well; working quickly, drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool 5 minutes.
Yields: 3 dozen.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on top of cake mix (will almost completely cover top).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening and cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and spices.
Add to first mixture.
Chill good.
Form into balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Put onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook in crock-pot on low for 18 hours.
Remove peppers.
Use a fork and shred roast.
Place in deep plate or bowl and pour juice over. Serve.

title: herb stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Chop stems finely.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in skillet.
Saute mushroom caps briefly on both sides. Remove to shallow baking dish.
Melt remaining butter and saute stems and onions.
Remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs and remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix.
Spoon into caps.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cantaloupe sorbet
directions: Position
knife blade in food processor bowl; add cantaloupe and process until smooth.
Mix cantaloupe, sugar and lemon juice; stir well.
Cover and freeze until almost firm, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat soup and milk; dip tortillas in this mixture.
Place small amount of onions, chicken, green chilies and cheese on each tortilla.
Roll up and place in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over tortilla.
Sprinkle any remaining ingredients over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: edee's crab salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: cinnamon cream pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and cornstarch.
Stir in scalded milk; then very gradually, blend in beaten egg yolks.
Add the half stick of margarine, cut in several pieces.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool.

title: chinese whatsit(or you name it casserole)
directions: Saute beef; add salt and pepper to taste and a dash of sugar. Place cooked beef in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch baking casserole.
Combine celery and onion and layer evenly over beef.
Break up frozen peas and make another layer.
(Celery, onion and peas may be combined to make 1 layer together.)
Spread crushed potato chips over vegetables.
Dilute soup with water and pour over all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage cookies
directions: Lightly brown sausage in frying pan, breaking into pieces. Remove sausage to absorbent paper and reserve 1/4 cup drippings.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place roast in Dutch oven; add soup mix and mushroom soup. Add water to cover roast.
Cover.
Cook at 325° for about 2 hours. Add carrots and potatoes during last 45 minutes of cooking if desired.

title: farmers casserole
directions: Brown steak or boil chicken.
Saute onions and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cook, covered.

title: jello balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Roll into balls and roll in small box of Jell-O.
(Use red for Christmas; orange for Thanksgiving.)

title: mexican mess
directions: Brown meat with onion and spices; drain well. Add corn, picante, beans and tomatoes; simmer for 30 minutes.
Crush tortilla chips in a serving dish; spoon mixture over chips.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, taco sauce (if taco sauce used, I leave out other seasonings) and black olives.
Quick, easy and great!

title: a crock of beans and meatless sausage
directions: Add ingredients to crock-pot.
Let cook on high until thickened; about 4 to 6 hours.
Serve over brown rice, barley or bulgur wheat.

title: onions and rice
directions: Saute green onions in hot oil in a large skillet until tender. Add rice and next 5 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Garnish with a green onion fan.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and margarine.
Beat well and bake in an 8-inch greased pan in a hot oven, 400°, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into shell and bake at 300° until knife comes out clean when inserted in center.
Pie should be brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well, adding sugar slowly.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes a 1 pound loaf.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix together, 3/4 pkg. of chipped beef, (chopped) with cream cheese, onion, garlic powder and accent. Make into a ball and roll in reserved 1/4 pkg. chipped beef. Refrigerate until about 1/2 hour before serving. Serve with crackers.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour and mix with salt and soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
Bake in 3 greased layer pans at 350° until tested done. Let cool and frost.

title: new orleans pecan pie
directions: In saucepan, combine egg yolks, sour cream, granulated sugar, flour, vanilla and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened (about 5 to 10 minutes).
Pour into baked pie shell. Set aside.

title: sweet blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in with pastry blender the shortening, egg and milk.
Add blueberries.
Drop batter into cupcake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook down until thick.
Then can. Let set for 30 days before use.

title: country sausage and potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook and stir sausage and onion in oil in 10-inch or 12-inch skillet until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in potatoes, sauce mix, water and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Stir in carrot strips; cover and simmer until carrots are crisp-tender and potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Cover and cook until broccoli is heated through and cheese is melted, 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Toss
all
ingredients and place in crock-pot.	Cook on low-medium for
8 hours.
Mixture will thicken and be ready to eat!

title: pound cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, shortening, butter and vanilla until smooth. Add flour and beat on high for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pear cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Mix well and add pears.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
No icing needed for this moist cake.
Great way to use up pears during pear season.

title: bro. don's corn dish
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Set aside, keep drippings in pan.
Cut corn off with sharp knife, cutting first a thin layer off tops of kernels.
Repeat twice, getting all kernels off cob.

title: mexican potato topper
directions: Microwave on High for 5 minutes; stir and return if needed to melt cheese thoroughly.
Can also be used as topping for broccoli, cauliflower, etc.

title: ribbon fantasy fudge
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1/3 cup milk in heavy, 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 4 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add 1 cup (1/2 jar) Marshmallow Creme and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until well blended.

title: chicken and mushroom sauce
directions: Season chicken to taste.
Place in ovensafe pan.
Mix soup, milk and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: grapefruit and crab meat cocktail
directions: Chill grapefruit and crab meat in cans.
Drain grapefruit. Flake crab meat, removing bony tissue.
Alternate grapefruit and crab meat in cocktail glasses.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over grapefruit and crab meat.
Serves 8.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Make a paste of red coloring and cocoa; add to creamed ingredients.
Then add vanilla. Mix buttermilk in same cup where red coloring was mixed.
Use all clinging coloring.
Sift flour, salt and soda together and add to mixture.
Beat well; then fold in vinegar.
Pour into 2 cake pans lined with greased waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: corn 'n' dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dee's kitchen soup
directions: Brown meat in large pan; drain grease.
Celery and onion may be cooked at this time.
Add water, seasoning and tomatoes.
If using any fresh vegetables or rice, add at this time.
Cook until tender.
Add more water as needed.
More seasoning may be needed, depending on taste.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Serve with cornbread or biscuits.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt, cold water and shortening like for pie crust. Cut up apples and place in center.
Add butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Shape the dough around apple.
Jag around sides and top with fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Could possibly even take 1 hour. Keep checking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter in mixing bowl; add each of the following one at a time and stir until well mixed between each: Sugar, eggs, syrup, vanilla, salt, pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 55-60 minutes or until pie appears set.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a lightly greased pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for several hours before serving.

title: green enchiladas(get raves!!!)
directions: Combine soup, milk and Velveeta in top of double boiler.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add chilies and pimientos.
Set aside.
Brown meat; season with a little cumin powder and pepper, if desired. Layer torn tortillas, meat, onion, Velveeta sauce and grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Enjoy!

title: pavlova
directions: Line a baking sheet with foil.
Draw six (3-inch) circles on the foil.
Set aside.
In a small mixer bowl combine egg whites, vinegar and salt.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed until soft peaks form (tips curl).
Gradually add the 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating on high speed until very stiff peaks form (tips stand straight) and sugar is almost dissolved (about 4 minutes).
Use the back of a spoon to spread the meringue over the circles on the foil, building the sides up.
Bake in a 300° oven for 35 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Let meringue shells dry in oven, with door closed, for at least 1 hour.
Remove from foil.
To serve, spoon fruit into meringue shells.
Top with whipped topping.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broiled chicken(or maybe oiled-foil-broiled chicken)
directions: Marinate the chicken breasts in lemon juice and herbs de Provence for 8 to 24 hours.
Cover the broiler pan with aluminum foil, then oil the foil.
Heat the broiler.
Arrange the chicken on the oiled foiled pan; broil
it on one side, then turn it over and broil it on the other side.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well and set aside.
Cook rice (not instant) and set aside.
Saute chopped celery and onion in melted margarine over low heat.
Stir frequently until wilted.
Add cream of chicken soup and milk. Simmer until well mixed.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir well until melted into mixture.
Add rice, broccoli and salt and pepper to taste with 3 good dashes of Tabasco sauce.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into large casserole.
Top with breadcrumbs and grated mild Cheddar cheese (optional).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and hot. Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: roast stuffed turkey
directions: Rinse turkey thoroughly inside and out.
Using your hands, rub turkey completely with vegetable oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place bread in bottom of roasting pan.
Put turkey, breast side down, on the bread.
Cook in 400° oven for 1 hour. Remove turkey from oven and place on large platter (we use oven mitts to turn the turkey onto its back).
Make the stuffing (recipe following), using the bread in the bottom of the roasting pan.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add eggs, cheese, mushrooms, onion and dash of salt and pepper.
Mix well; set aside.
Cook manicotti according to directions (don't cook too long it makes the noodles hard to stuff).
Stuff with hamburger mixture and layer in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with sauce and a little grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender.
Remove from broth.
Cook pack of noodles in broth.
Saute mushrooms, onions and green peppers in butter and garlic.
Stir into noodles and broth.
Add stewed tomatoes and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add 1 tablespoon cornstarch with enough water to make a smooth paste.
Add to other ingredients.
Serve with salad and rolls.
Enjoy!!

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook cheese and soup together until smooth.
Combine all ingredients in greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix baking mix, milk, brown sugar, oleo and nutmeg.
Spread in ungreased square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Drain peaches, reserving 1 cup syrup. Arrange peaches on mixture in pan. Pour reserved syrup over peaches. Bake until golden brown, about 40 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
You can use fruit cocktail (30 ounces) for the peaches.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Use big zucchini, but still tender enough so you can pierce the skin easily with your thumbnail.
Peel, cut into quarters lengthwise, remove the seeds and slice crosswise.
Add zucchini to remaining ingredients after they are tossed together.
Mix well. (It may be runny.)
Dump into a 9-inch pie crust and bake 40 minutes at 400° or until golden brown.
(You'll think you are eating apple pie, but it's more delicious.)

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Can be served warm or cold. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries very well. Mold into a ball and refrigerate overnight. Roll in chopped pecans before serving. This is always a favorite at parties.

title: jeff's potato salad with beer dressing
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender. Peel and slice.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz and soup together.
Add chicken, then Veg-All. Pour into casserole dish. Crush 1 tube Ritz crackers and melt 1/4 stick margarine.
Toss together and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: corn chowder
directions: Dice potatoes and onion; cook in grease from bacon slices until tender.
Add celery soup and milk.
Heat through.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: cherry cream puff ring
directions: Puff:
Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to boiling in a 1-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously about 1 minute until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet to form an 8-inch ring.*
Smooth top with spatula.
Bake until puffed and golden, 50 to 60 minutes.
Cut off top with sharp knife.
Pull out any soft dough.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash,
onion, flour, pepper, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs and add to squash.
Add margarine.
Drop by tablespoons on oiled griddle.
Cook on both sides until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Break up cheese and mix in remaining ingredients until smooth. (Or place all in a blender and process until smooth.)
If the dressing is too thick, add a little milk to make it pour better.

title: almond tea
directions: Mix well.
Before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream
sugar
and
butter
or
softened margarine.
Add eggs; mix
well.
Add 1/2 of the flour, salt and baking powder to
the creamed
sugar
mixture.
Then add water, vanilla and remainder of flour mixture.
Form into small balls on greased cookie
sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: cheesy ham and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together potatoes, oleo, salt, pepper, soup, ham, onion and sour cream.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Crumble with Topping.

title: banana snack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, butter and walnuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together.
Spread over cool crust.
Mix lemon pudding and cold milk together to make third layer.
Top with thin layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon-orange salad
directions: Mix jello and 2 cups hot water.
Stir in frozen orange juice. Cool.
Then add mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix all well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Works well in tube pan or layers.

title: gratin potatoes(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Rub the inside of 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish with the cut garlic clove; let it dry.
Then smear the inside of the dish with butter or margarine.
Cut potatoes into slices no thicker than 1/8-inch.
Arrange slices in dish in rows, slightly overlapping both slices and rows.
Lightly salt each layer.
Do not fill dish more than 2/3 full.
Pour milk into dish until potatoes are about half covered; then just barely cover the whole mixture with the half and half.
Finally, sprinkle all liberally with the bread crumbs and some butter shavings.
(Note:
I use plain skim milk; relying on the seasoned crouton crumbs for flavor; it works fine!)

title: mexican soup
directions: Cook meat; drain.
In a large pot, add additional ingredients for 30 minutes.
Serve with cornbread.

title: grease and flour pan
directions: Mix together.
Store in refrigerator and use on pans when recipes read, "grease and flour pans."
Works great on special occasion cake pans.

title: whole note chicken
directions: Put celery, pepper and onion in melted oleo in a skillet.
Cook until almost done.
Cook 2 cups rice which will make 4 cups cooked rice.
Mix chicken, rice, soup and cooked items together.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
The last 10 minutes, put cheese on top; bake until melted and a little brown on top.

title: orange fluff
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan (don't drain).
Boil and remove from burner.
Add jello and stir to dissolve.
Add the cold water and slightly congeal.
Fold in ground cheese.
Add the Cool Whip and nuts, folding.
Put in casserole dish and chill.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion; drain off fat.
Add beans, brown sugar, white sugar, vinegar, mustard, catsup, salt and pepper. Place in baking dish and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: tex mex dip
directions: In the bottom of a serving dish spread the bean dip, set aside. Mix together the avocado dip, lemon juice and picante sauce and spread over the bean dip. Mix together the mayonnaise and sour cream, spread this over the avocado mixture. Then sprinkle with the seasoning. Top with tomatoes, onions and cheese.

title: choco peanut butter dreams
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together sugar, peanut butter and margarine until light and fluffy. Blend in water, egg and vanilla. Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: baked turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Baste turkey with magarine.
Stuff if desired.
Put water, onion and apple in roaster.
Put turkey, breast side down in water (this keeps the breast basted and moist).
Cover roaster.
Bake at 475° for one hour.
Turn oven off.
Do not open oven door at all all night.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate in double boiler or microwave oven.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Cool in refrigerator about 30 minutes until edges harden.
Chill again until completely hardened.

title: tante herta's green tomato relish(this is a double recipe)
directions: Put tomatoes, onions and peppers through coarse grinder; add salt and let drain real dry.
Put tomatoes, vinegar, sugar and spices in pot.
Add red pepper and bring to a good boil. Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring well.
Pour into jars and process in the recommended manner.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Slightly beat the eggs in a blender.
Add pumpkin, sugars, salt and spices.
Add milk last and beat until mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot (425°) oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: venison stew
directions: Put in 5-quart stockpot, venison meat that is cut into chunks (as big as you like), onion, salt and pepper.
Add water to cover meat; add bouillon cubes.
Cover; let cook until meat is done. Put in potatoes and carrots (chopped); cook until done.
Add canned vegetables as stated.
Simmer.
Add flour and water in separate bowl, make it pasty.
Add salt and pepper.
Add to stew, stirring constantly until thickened.
Let simmer; serve.

title: baked shrimp a la jessica
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine first 9 ingredients in shallow 2-quart baking dish and mix well.
Remove 1/4 cup of this mixture and set aside.
Add shrimp to baking dish and mix thoroughly. Combine bread crumbs with reserved butter sauce and sprinkle over shrimp.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: best ever cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute beef and onion lightly.
Do not brown; drain fat. Remove from heat.
Add rice and water and mix.
Place 1/2 of cabbage into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Put rest of cabbage over meat.
Pour soup over all. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Dice all fruit.
Cut up nuts. Add grated coconut. Dredge with 3 cups flour.
Cream the butter, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Add remaining cup of flour.
Pour this batter over dredged fruit and nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Bake in oven about 275° for about 2 hours.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: In small bowl, combine mayo, pepper and chili sauce.
Spread about 1 tablespoon of this mixture on each bread slice.
On each of 4 bread slices, place a cheese slice, 1/4 of the corned beef, 1/4 of the sauerkraut, a cheese slice and another bread slice, mayo side down.

title: k's brownies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add flour, melted margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, salt and onion; let stand 2 hours. Drain well. Pack in freezer containers, leaving 1-inch headspace.

title: norma's creamy apricot salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/2 cup juice and set aside. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add marshmallows, stirring until slightly melted.
Stir in the pineapple and apricot baby food.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg
white.
Combine cream cheese and the reserved pineapple juice, blending well. Stir in whipped topping.
Fold in gleatin mixture.
Arrange banana slices in bottom of a lightly greased 12 x 18 x 2-inch Pyrex dish. Spoon gelatin mixture over bananas.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts (pecans).
Chill until firm.
Yields 12 servings.
A pretty orange color and delicious.

title: bug sandwich
directions: Take 2 pieces of plain bread, put dead spiders and flies and their guts on top.
Put fur on it and roast it for 16,000 days. Roast it in a 36 oven.
Turn it up to 70 or 80°.
Then eat it.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Drain and serve.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender and drain. Add corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mud pie
directions: Make crust with cookies and oleo and refrigerate.
Soften ice cream and add to chilled crust.
Add sauce before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Finely chop green onions and chipped beef.
Mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple and set juice aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour pie filling in to cover bottom.
Put drained or crushed pineapple on top of that.
Pour dry cake mix on top of pineapple and spread evenly.
Pour melted butter and pineapple juice on top of dry cake mix.
Mix coconut and brown sugar together and spread over top of juice.
Cover top of cake sufficiently.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until coconut is golden brown.
Cherry juice should be coming through top.

title: pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix sugar and butter together.
Add flour and eggs alternately, beginning and ending with flour (example: flour, 2 eggs, flour, 2 eggs, flour and etc.).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Drain and season with salt and pepper.
Mix with 1/2 stuffing.
Add sour cream, pimentos, onion and soup.
Mix other half stuffing with half cup melted butter.
Line casserole with half stuffing; pour squash mixture into casserole.
Top with rest of stuffing. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pol's apple cake
directions: Mix in saucepan for 3 minutes;
pour over warm cake.

title: mexican fri chik
directions: Saute onion and green chilies until onion is soft.
Add to remaining ingredients except tortillas and Cheddar cheese.
Grease a 3-quart casserole dish.
Place a layer of tortillas in the bottom of the pan.
Spoon some chicken mixture on tortillas and continue layering tortillas and chicken mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour.
Top servings with your favorite picante sauce.
Serves 8.

title: lazy man cobbler
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend.
Melt margarine in pan.
Add milk mixture.
Stir in canned peaches. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until browned.

title: potatoes with herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine seasonings.
Place 2 tablespoons oleo in nonstick skillet and melt.
Arrange 1/3 of potatoes in a circular pattern, with about 1/4 of seasoning, 1/3 onion and 2 tablespoons soft oleo.
Repeat layers 2 times.
Cover tightly with foil and press down.
Bake 20 minutes uncovered. Bake 20 minutes.
Uncover; bake 20 minutes more or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven; press down with spatula.
Let stand 10 minutes; remove to a platter.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry crunch salad
directions: Mix and spread in greased Pyrex 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: crunchy chicken cheese bake
directions: In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, place chicken.
Top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese; top with tomato. Combine margarine and stuffing; sprinkle over tomato.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, milk, salt and oleo in saucepan; cook until it comes to a boil.
Boil only 1 minute and remove from heat, then mix in oatmeal and other ingredients.
Place in buttered pan or drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Makes 3 to 5 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Add cheese, Bisquick and water.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Can also be frozen and cooked when needed.

title: benedictine spread
directions: In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, beat cheese until smooth and creamy.
Slice cucumber in half lengthwise.
Scrape pulp and seeds into a small sieve.
Place sieve over a cup and, with the back of a spoon, push juice from pulp (if more juice is needed, rub peeled cucumber over sieve to extract juice).
Add cucumber juice, onion, mayonnaise, Tabasco, Worcestershire and only enough green coloring to give a faint green tint.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Correct seasoning, if necessary.
Refrigerate.

title: individual cheese cake
directions: Place piece of graham cracker in bottom of muffin paper.
Beat well the cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Pour over grahams and top with pie filling.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 12 to 15.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a preheated oven at 475° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef with noodles
directions: Place a clean towel over wire cooling rack.
Spread cooked noodles evenly over towel and let dry 3 hours.
Combine water, 2 teaspoons soy sauce, salt and bouillon granules in a small bowl. Cut beef across the grain into thin slices, about 2 inches long.

title: kraut relish
directions: Combine sauerkraut, carrot, green pepper and green onion.
Mix together Italian salad dressing and poppy seed.
Add to vegetables and toss well to coat.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings, 39 calories per serving.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop batter by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° about 8 minutes.

title: potato stuffing or dressing
directions: Cook potatoes.
Add salt.
Drain.
Add oleo and mash.
Fry onions and celery until tender.
Add to potatoes.
Add bread, egg and poultry seasoning.
Mix can be used to stuff a small chicken or put in greased bowl, cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Take foil off to brown top.
Good as a side dish with fried chicken.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add milk gradually, stirring until smooth. Melt butter in iron skillet and add mixture; cook until thick.

title: homos bi tahini
directions: Bring to a boil the contents of the can of garbanzo beans and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Save the juice from the beans to be used later if the mixture is too thick and needs thinning.
Using a food processor, place all the ingredients (with the exception of the olive oil, paprika and parsley twigs) and blend until mixture is smooth.
Taste to see if you want to add more lemon juice or salt to mixture.
Pour into a nice serving dish; drizzle olive oil on top.
