Sprinkle with paprika and add a couple of parsley twigs for added decoration.
Pita bread can be cut into triangles and used to dip into Homos.
I usually double this recipe which serves 6 to 8 people.
Import stores have the tahini.

title: aunt winnie's carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs for 1 minute.
Separately combine flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add the 2 mixtures together.
Fold in the carrots and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Blend by hand and roll into 1-inch balls.
Should make about 1 dozen.
Freeze on cookie sheet and put in Ziploc bags.
Bake when needed at 350° for about 15 minutes or until firm and slightly browned.

title: dreamy cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries (medium grind).
Pour sugar over cranberries and let set.
Wash grapes, cut in half.
Put marshmallows in same bowl with grapes.
Mix chopped pecans, grapes, marshmallows and cranberries all together.
Whip the cream and mix thoroughly.
It is better for cranberries, grapes, nuts and marshmallows to sit in refrigerator overnight, then mix with whipped cream about 2 to 4 hours before serving, but this is not necessary.
Serves 12.

title: rumbledethumps
directions: Cook cabbage a few minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon.
In the same water, cook potatoes until done.
Mash potatoes and butter with masher.
In casserole stir all 4 ingredients together and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown beef in shortening.
Add water and simmer in covered skillet for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender.
Add more water, if needed. Serve on buns.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except cocktail sauce together.
Form ball.
Refrigerate several hours.
Before serving, pour sauce on top.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Saute meat with chopped onion; mix with eggplant which has been cooked and drained. Crumble crackers and add to meat mixture along with eggplant. Put in greased casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cube steak casserole
directions: Roll cube steak in flour; salt and pepper to taste; brown in greased skillet on both sides.
Place meat in casserole dish or crock-pot.
Mix soup, gravy, and water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook 2 hours at 350° in casserole dish, or start on high for 1/2 hour in crock-pot, then cook on low until tender.

title: lung fever salve - draw salve
directions: First put the lard and wax together and melt; then melt camphor in
it.
Then
put in all the other ingredients except for turpentine
and
cook
until
they are all melted.
Remove from stove
and
then add turpentine (turpentine is inflammable).

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix together; form into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Top with a cherry.

title: weight watchers casserole
directions: Mix all together in a large baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: louella's broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: chicken skanavis
directions: Put chicken in a casserole and cover with Swiss cheese.
Pour over the breast, the can of soup which has been diluted with sherry.
Top with stuffing and drizzle the melted butter over all. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: apple pudding
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch baking dish. Cream 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup butter. Add eggs. Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add to creamed mixture. Mix in apples. Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clam dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add sage to taste and bake in greased baking dish at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease (not oil) and flour bottoms only of two 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.

title: egg rolls
directions: Stir-fry cabbage, carrots and onions in 2 tablespoons oil and soy sauce for one minute.
Remove from wok and set aside.
Add meat and salt and pepper to vegetables.
Heat 2 cups oil in a skillet.
Spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons of mixture on each egg roll wrapper, fold sides and roll diagonally.
Brush with water to seal.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with onion until tender.
Drain.
Mix in salt, milk and cup of cheese (about 4 slices) until cheese melts.
Pour a layer of potato-milk mixture in a casserole dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Continue layering potato mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, margarine and vanilla; add coconut, raisins and pecans. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage with fried apples
directions: Shape sausage into 12 patties.
Fry in a large skillet over low heat until well done but not crisp.
Remove to heated platter; keep warm.
Pour off all but 4 tablespoons drippings.
Core apples but do not pare.
Cut into rings about 1/2-inch thick.
Arrange apple slices in skillet.
Top with grape jelly and cinnamon.
Cook over low heat.
Cover for several minutes to soften apples. Uncover; cook until apples are tender and well glazed; turn often, being careful to keep shape of apples.
Arrange on platter with sausage.
Garnish with grape glaze.
Serve immediately.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together in mixer until smooth. Refrigerate.
This dip is great with fresh vegetables.

title: beef paprika
directions: Cube beef.
Heat drippings in a large skillet or flame-proof casserole.	Add
beef
and fry until brown on all sides. Peel and chop
onions
and garlic.
Add to pan and cook until transparent. Sprinkle
in
flour
and stir into mixture.
Add broth, marjoram, caraway
seed, a pinch of sugar, paprika and seasonings.
Cover tightly and cook gently for 1 3/4 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion; add potatoes, soup, cheese, sour cream and seasonings.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Mix melted margarine with crumbs.
Pat into a crust, covering potatoes, during the last 10 minutes of baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese custard
directions: Boil macaroni in
generous
amount of water.
Drain and mix with grated
cheese,
salt	and
butter.
Lastly,
stir in eggs. Pour in greased baking dish and bake to light brown.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Reserve 1/4 of potato
chips
to
crumble on top.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In large bowl, mix Cool Whip, pudding and pineapple.
Then add mandarin oranges and marshmallows.
Pour into mold or bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: babuska peanut butter triangle cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and butter with powdered sugar until well blended.
Stir in Rice Krispies and options.
Roll into 4-inch triangles or your size you like.
Roll in finely chopped nuts and chill.
Slice as needed.

title: toasted pita triangles
directions: Cut pita bread into quarters; separate into 2 pieces.
Cream together softened butter with herbs and seasonings.
Spread each pita piece with herb butter.
Place pita pieces on baking sheet and bake at 375° until butter is melted and pita is crispy, about 5 to 8 minutes.

title: lime melon balls
directions: Boil together the water and sugar.
Cool to room temperature and add lime juice.
Pour over melon balls in sherbet glasses. Garnish with pomegranate seeds, a sprig of mint or thin slices of lime.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with whisk until well blended (1 to 2 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: blueberry-almond blintzes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter, in a food processor or blender until smooth.
Heat an 8-inch crepe pan or skillet over medium heat.
Coat pan with about 1/2 teaspoon of butter.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons of batter to the butter, tilting pan to make an even layer of batter.
Cook on one side only.
When bottom begins to brown, turn out to cool on a plate.
Repeat process with remaining batter.
Makes 18.

title: banana cream cake
directions: Mash bananas.
Mix well sugar, oil, eggs and salt.
Mix flour, spices, soda and pecans (optional).
Alternate flour mixture and bananas into the sugar mixture.
Bake in two 9-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan; grease well.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
After cooled ice with cream cheese mix.
It makes for smiles.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Mix soups, water, rice and parsley in bottom of flat baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of mixture and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover with foil; bake 2 hours at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: zucchini
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter; add quartered zucchini. Cook until tender.
Add diced tomato and/or 1 can chili with or without beans.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cheese and cover to let cheese melt and serve.

title: "pink christmas" frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix in all ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in paper liners in muffin tins and freeze.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 12.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in flour, egg yolks, lemon peel and juice, and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff, fold into first mixture.
Pour into pie shell and bake in preheated oven.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 45 minutes until golden or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine both the cream cheese and American cheese in a bowl. Add the garlic powder.
Roll into a ball.
Put the chili powder (as much as needed) on a plate.
Roll the cheese ball around until it is covered with chili powder.
Serve with crackers.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix flour and sugar.

title: ground beef with cornbread(serves 4)
directions: Brown beef, pepper, onions and	salt.
Add chili powder and tomato sauce.
(If there is any
grease, drain well.) Pour beef and tomato mixture into oiled 9
x	13-inch
baking dish. Pour beans over meat mixture.
Spread
cheese
over beans; set aside.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill well before serving.

title: broiled red snapper
directions: Place snapper on broiler pan. Brush with butter and squeeze a slice of lemon over each piece of fish.
Sprinkle with a small amount of oregano and just a hint of paprika.
Broil on top rack of oven for approximately 5 to 6 minutes.
Crack door to keep fish warm until serving.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add slightly beaten eggs, sweet milk, vanilla and nutmeg and stir well.
Mix buttermilk and soda and then add to the mixture.
Mix in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll thin, cut into strips lengthwise and then across to make squares and rectangles.
Place in greased pans and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 dozen tea cakes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle lemon juice over.
Combine cake mix, nuts and melted butter.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: "icebox" pickles
directions: Bring ingredients, except cucumbers and onions, to boil. Alternate cucumbers and onions in jar.
Pour hot liquid over cucumbers and onions.
Let cool.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: cooked icing
directions: Combine flour and milk in a saucepan, adding milk slowly, and stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Set aside to chill completely.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind together first 5 ingredients.
Add pineapple and sugar. Dissolve jello and hot water.
Cool.
Add fruit mixture and refrigerate 4 hours.

title: just for kids dough and salt art
directions: Knead flour and salt together adding water gradually.
Arrange art shapes on cookie sheet and brush with egg whites before baking.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Art will be 1/2-inch thick.

title: braised cabbage
directions: In skillet heat butter until foamy.
Add chives and sauce until tender.
Add green cabbage and carrots.

title: christmas rum balls
directions: Combine wafers and next three ingredients.
Mix in pecans, syrup and rum.
Blend well.
Dust hands with sugar and shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Press pecans in top of each ball.
Let stand for 1 hour, then roll in sugar.
Store in tightly closed jar for 3 days.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook lima beans until done.
Mix 6 cups flour, 1 pint salt, eggs and water; roll dough and let dry 2 to 3 hours.
Melt Crisco in little frying pan; let it get real hot and add 4 tablespoons flour one at a time so it doesn't get lumpy.
Let brown and add 2 tablespoons garlic salt and 1 tablespoon paprika.
Add to lima beans and water they were cooked in.
Tear up dough and put in last.
Dig in.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix preceding ingredients with just enough water until dough forms.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut into pieces and deep fry until golden.
Top with honey or powdered sugar.

title: amish cream pie
directions: Heat milk, sugar and cornstarch in pan until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir and pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, oats, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In a small bowl, mix egg, water and oil; add all at once to oat mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in blueberries.
Spoon into greased or lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Blend 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over the batter in each muffin cup.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.
Muffins freeze well.
Microwave for a quick breakfast.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine 1 c. water and 1/4 c. butter and bring to a boil.
Add 1 c. flour and 1/2 tsp baking powder to above mixture.
Let cool. Beat in 3 eggs, 1 at a time.
Drop by Tbsp in soup and cover.
Cook about 20 minutes.

title: pasta salad (with fruit)
directions: Boil pasta 10 minutes; drain and cool.
Drain fruits, saving juice.
Add to juice the eggs and flour and cook until thick.
Add to pasta.
Fold in fruit.
Before serving, add about 10 ounces Cool Whip.

title: coconut supreme dessert
directions: Mix butter and flour until creamy.
Add pecans and press mixture onto bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake crust at 325° for 15 minutes (or until slightly golden).
Toast coconut in same oven.
Watch carefully for it browns quickly.
Next, mix 1 cup powdered sugar and the cream cheese.
Add 1 carton Cool Whip to this mixture and spread mixture over the baked crust.
Prepare instant pudding according to directions.
Allow pudding to set before spreading over cheese layer.
Cover pudding with 2nd carton of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain grease. Add the rest of the ingredients. Don't drain the vegetables. Bring to a boil and simmer.

title: barbecued duck breasts
directions: Dissolve soda and salt in bowl of water.
Soak duck breasts in this water 3 hours.
Remove, pat dry, and place in shallow pan. Combine next 5 ingredients in plastic bag.
Add duck breasts, close bag and marinate at least 1
1/2 hours (or overnight in refrigerator).
Remove breasts form marinade.
Wrap each in bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Cook on grill for about 5 minutes on each side, basting with marinade.
Serves 4.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add brown sugar. Cook 2 minutes. Stir constantly. Add milk. Cook until mixture boils. Remove from heat and cool 10 minutes. Beat in confectioners sugar.

title: secret message cookies
directions: Melt chips in a small saucepan over low heat and stir constantly.
Place on graham cracker on top of another and dip 3 sides in melted chocolate to seal, allowing excess to drip off. Place on wax paper until set.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a rolling boil (do not overcook). Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Add cornflakes; mix well.
Shape by rolling small balls in wet hands.
Let set on waxed paper 1/2 hour.
Do not double recipe.

title: classic karo pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter, and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50-55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool. Makes 8 servings.

title: hungarian cheese logs
directions: Mix with mixer.
Roll into 6 rolls on wax paper.
Sprinkle chili powder on wax paper and roll log in it.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Without draining them, mash until size of pea.
Meanwhile, cook onion in margarine for 3 minutes. Sprinkle with flour.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring often, 5 to 7 minutes until simmering and thickened.
Stir in potato mixture and remaining ingredients. Yields 4 servings, 234 calories.

title: apples and sweet potatoes
directions: Boil first six ingredients until thick.
Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Layer sweet potatoes and apples (apples need to be sliced thin).
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cook for 30 minutes in moderate (350°) oven.

title: macaroni and tomato soup
directions: Cook the macaroni.
Cook the ground beef with the onion and drain.
Add the milk to the tomato soup and heat.
Add the cooked macaroni and meat.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Cut dried beef in small pieces.
Chop onions fine and mix with cream cheese and 2/3 of the dried beef together with other ingredients.
Roll into a ball or log with hands.
Roll ball in remaining dried beef.
Refrigerate and set out 30 minutes before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together and applesauce.
Mix raisins with 1/2 cup flour.
Sift remaining flour with spices, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to liquid mixture.
Beat well. Pour into oiled pan.
Bake in very moderate oven 300° to 325° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: I double this and bake at 350° for an hour.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Sprinkle steak with paprika and set aside while preparing other ingredients.
Brown garlic in margarine and add steak, onions and green peppers.
Continue cooking until vegetables are wilted.
Add tomatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer on low heat about 15 minutes.
Blend water with cornstarch and soy sauce. Stir into steak.
Cook until thickened.
Serve over fluffy rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: fried squash sticks
directions: Slice squash in sticks.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll squash sticks and fry until golden brown.

title: delicious broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli flowerets, chopped dates, bacon, onion and nuts or seeds in a large bowl.
In separate bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and milk.
Pour over salad, mix well and serve!

title: ice cream(no cooking)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and beat with a mixer until well
blended.
Stir
in
any flavoring that you want to choose, such as:
strawberries, bananas, chocolate, etc.
Pour into freezer.
This
does not have a canned milk taste.	Makes about 5 quarts, depending on how much fruit is added.

title: cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Mix and dissolve cream cheese in sugar and a little cream. Cook sugar, syrup and cold water until dissolved.
Soften gelatin in cold water; add to juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, cheese and whipped cream.
Add English walnuts if desired.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together and pour in a buttered casserole dish.

title: holiday cut outs
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and beat until light.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Add cream; mix very well.
Chill several hours.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness. Decorate, after cutting out, with tree, angel, bell, etc., cutters.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen. Dough can be made and frozen.

title: karen's banana bread
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Mix Crisco oil and sugar. Add eggs.
Add flour mixture until well blended.
Add bananas and nuts, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 375° until golden brown or approximately 45 minutes (use average loaf pan).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil fryer; take the meat off the bone.
Mix stuffing according to package directions.
Mix each can of soup separately with a can of milk until creamy.
Layer in casserole dish in this order: half stuffing mix, chicken meat, cream of celery soup, half stuffing mix and cream of chicken soup.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: homemade pimento and cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use on bread, crackers or as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Place a layer of graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine oleo, sugar, milk and egg and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add crumbs, pecans and vanilla.
Spread this mixture on top of graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers. Combine oleo, milk and powdered sugar and spread over top of graham crackers.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Flatten on cookie sheets and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in 11 x 13-inch pan or casserole. Dilute soup with 1/2 can water in a bowl; stir and set aside. Combine Ro-Tel tomatoes with salsa and set aside.
Layer all ingredients in pan, starting with chips and ending with cheese and chips.
You may make 2 or 3 layers of each ingredient.
Bake about 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
grease
and
flour a tube pan. Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed. Scrape bowl
often.
Bake
at
350° for 1 hour in tube pan.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: melting moments cookies
directions: Sift cornstarch with flour.
Cream butter and sugar; add flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork dipped in water, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: depression days vegetable salad
directions: Mix salt, vinegar and water and pour over vegetables and let marinate a couple of hours or overnight.
More salt and vinegar can be added to suit taste.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Fry ground beef and drain; add spaghetti sauce, let sit.
In large bowl, mix cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour 1 cup of sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan and add layer of uncooked lasagne.
Cover with 1 1/4 cups of sauce and 1/3 of cheese mix.
Continue with layer of lasagne, sauce and cheese mix.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken sour cream enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces. Set aside. Mix chicken soup, chilies and sour cream. Place a layer of tortillas (whole or strips) in bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Spoon on soup mixture, then chicken pieces. Sprinkle with cheese. Repeat all layers. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and cool. Drain artichokes, reserving 1/4 cup liquid; set aside. Cut artichokes into fourths. Set aside. Combine pasta, artichokes, reserved artichoke liquid and remaining ingredients in a large bowl; toss gently. Cover and chill. Yield: 6 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and cut raw potatoes into quarters and then into 1/2-inch slices.
Put in pot and barely cover with water.
Add onion, parsley, salt, caraway, marjoram and bay leaf.
Cook until potatoes are soft.
Make a roux from the butter and flour and add a little water from the cooked potatoes to thin.
Add this back to the potato mixture to thicken.
Stir in vinegar as desired for taste.

title: marshmallow creme
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to 242° or medium ball stage. While this mixture is cooking, place the Karo syrup and egg whites into a bowl.
Beat slowly until mixed, then beat hard until light and fluffy.
Pour the first mixture into this in a fine stream.
When the mixture is completely combined, beat hard for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and store in jars or cans.
Do not cover until mixture is cold.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Combine in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon in jars and seal. To serve, add 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and ginger. Add to first mixture.
Put in refrigerator to cool (easier to handle).
Shape in small balls (flour hands to make easy).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 minutes at 375°.
Dust with powdered sugar while warm.
Makes 4 1/2 to 6 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saut celery in butter until tender. Combine soup and cheese in large bowl. Mix in broccoli and rice; pour in dish. Bake 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: miami "vise"
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; cover and process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: easy shrimp
directions: Melt butter in blazer pan or chafing dish.
Add garlic and cool slightly.
Add shrimp; cook, stirring frequently, until shrimp are tender.
Stir in wine and parsley.
Heat to boiling. Serve with rice.

title: ranch-spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve in hollowed out round bread loaf.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease or spray bottom of 9x13 inch pan. Sprinkle pecans and coconut over bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions on the box and pour over pecans and coconut mixture.
Mix cream cheese, butter, and sugar together. Pour over cake mixture, leaving 1/2 to 1 inch on each side.
Bake for 50 minutes.
This was always a favorite of Muggsy's when he came to the house.
Without nuts, of course.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti. Mix together soups, chicken and cooked spaghetti. Top with cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta just enough so it is soft enough to roll.
Don't overcook.
Drain and lay flat on foil to cool.
Combine Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper in bowl.
Spread cheese filling on each noodle.
Top with a little sauce, then roll them up.
Place in baking dish seam side down.
Top with more sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Continue to bake until cheese melts.

title: eggplant parmegiana
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Place in shallow dish.
Dip eggplant slices in egg and then in flour mixture.
Brown slices until golden in hot oil.
Drain well on brown paper.
Place one layer of eggplant in glass 8 x 8-inch baking dish; top with half of Parmesan cheese, Italian sauce and Mozzarella.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is completely melted.

title: fried okra
directions: Dip okra in
egg mixture, then in flour mixture.
Fry in hot deep fat.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix margarine, flour, brown sugar and oats.
In separate bowl mix cranberry sauce and sugar.
Grease cake pan with a little melted butter.
Spread 1/2 of oats mixture in cake pan.
Spread cranberry sauce mixture over oats mixture, then cover cranberry mixture with remaining oats mixture.
Bake in 375° oven until golden brown.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla at medium speed for 3 or 4 minutes.
Gradually add flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on a wire rack for 20 minutes. Dribble with brown sugar topping while warm.

title: healthful date bread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine dates and raisins.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.

title: louise's oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water; drain raisins, saving 1/3 cup juice. Cream shortening; add sugar and cream again.
Add beaten eggs. Stir in oats.
Sift flour with spices, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with 1/3 cup raisin water.
Add nuts and raisins.
Spoon onto cookie sheet with tablespoon or roll into balls by hand.
Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly brown at 350°. Do not overbake or the cookies will be hard.

title: fresh apple or pear cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Combine apples, eggs and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Add pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in a 17 x 11 x 1-inch pan and pat together. Bake at 350° until light brown, 10 to 11 minutes.
Cool.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in oblong pan.
Put crushed pineapple on baked cake.
then add vanilla pudding.
Add sliced bananas, then add Cool Whip (spread across bananas), cherries (drain juice and crush), pecans (crushed) and coconut on top (optional).
Keep refrigerated.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Butter bread placing buttered side on bottom of pan.
Layer the Cheddar cheese, Velveeta cheese and ham, sausage or bacon on top of bread.
If bacon or sausage is used, brown and fry.
Mix the rest of ingredients together and pour on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1/2 hour, covered, then 1 hour uncovered in a 350° oven.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: pork tenderloin with onion-raisin sauce
directions: Brown tenderloin.
Place in 275° oven until done, slightly pink in middle.
In separate pan, heat 1 tablespoon butter or oil. Saute onion until caramelized.
Add raisins.
Mix wine and cornstarch.
Add to onion and raisins.
Cook until thick.
Slice tenderloin; place on sauce.
Serve with vegetable and potato or rice.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt, then add milk, shortening and vanilla.
Beat well until fluffy.
Mix in nuts and pour into well-greased and floured pan (about 7 x 10-inch pan).

title: fettucini with tomatoes, basil and feta cheese
directions: Mix tomatoes, Prosciutto, basil, olive oil, vinegar and garlic in large bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside for 1/2 hour.
Cook pasta in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Add pasta to tomato mixture.
Top with Feta cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: chinese chicken slaw
directions: Whisk dressing and soy sauce together and set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients (except chow mein noodles). Pour dressing over salad and toss well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve topped with Chinese noodles.
(This is really good over hot white rice, too.)

title: creamy chicken paprikash
directions: This is a lean and light dish that is ready to eat in 30 minutes.

title: layered salad deluxe
directions: Layer spinach,
lettuce,
eggs, bacon and peas in order listed in a large salad bowl.

title: yummy salad
directions: Combine lettuce, carrot, and onion in large salad bowl.
Cook bacon slices and save bacon grease for later.
Crumble bacon into small bits.
Mix ramen noodles and almonds on a cookie sheet. Lightly coat the noodle/almond mixture with the bacon grease. Brown the mixture in toaster (or conventional) oven.
Make dressing by combining vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, and soy sauce in a sauce pan.
Simmer sauce until sugar is dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Add bacon bits and the toasted ramen noodles and almonds to salad in bowl.
Mix and serve.
Keep dressing separate from salad until salad is served.
(Salad will not keep very long once dressing is added.)

title: quick berry punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid and cranberry juice cocktail.
Just before serving, add 7-Up.

title: hamburger-stuffed bread loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice top off of loaf and set aside. Remove bread from interior of loaf, leaving enough on the sides to form a shell.
Tear the bread you removed into small pieces in a mixing bowl.
Brown the ground beef and drain well.
Return to pan and add onion; cook until onion starts to get soft.
Add green pepper (and celery if using) and mix well.
Add Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Add meat mixture to bread pieces in bowl. Mix well; mix in the undiluted soup.
Taste test and adjust seasoning.
Stuff bread loaf shell with mixture.
Top with cheese. If desired, spread butter or margarine on the top slice you removed.
(You can also sprinkle it with garlic powder or more of the cheese.)
Heat stuffed loaf (and top) on a cookie sheet in preheated oven approximately 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Slice and serve.

title: fun donuts
directions: You will also need a paper bag for shaking donuts.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pot and chill well.
(I add the cold ginger ale right before serving.
This can be frozen if you make it ahead of time.)
Makes approximate 128 ounces; twenty (6 ounce) servings.

title: angel chocolate and raspberry dream(fat-free)
directions: Use an 8-inch square glass baking dish or similar size.
Cut half of the cake and cut it in half.
Using 1/4 of the cake, break into bite size pieces and make a layer of cake pieces in the bottom of the dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup of raspberries over the pieces of cake.

title: never fail dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add the biscuit mix and mix well. Knead about 1 minute on a board dusted with flour.
Shape into rolls and put on lightly greased baking sheet or muffin tins. Cover with damp cloth and let rise in a warm place, about 1 hour. Cook in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato and pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and drain.
Peel potatoes and onion; slice thinly.
Layer pork chops alternately with onion and potato slices in casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix flour with milk and pour over layers.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all together.
Add tiny marshmallows and refrigerate. When serving, add 3 to 4 bananas.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Have pastry shell ready; heat oven to 425°.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to creamed mixture, gradually adding milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix after each addition.
Add flour and mix.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 23 to 30 minutes.

title: truffles
directions: Melt chocolate in a bowl over hot water.
Remove bowl from hot water and whisk in butter.
Next, whisk in egg yolks.
Add rum, cognac or liqueur.
Place bowl over cold water and beat vigorously until chocolate is thick and smooth.
Chill until workable.
Form into balls with 2 teaspoons; roll in unsweetened cocoa.
Place on a chilled plate until firm.
Roll in cocoa again and keep chilled in a covered container until served.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add coconut (not to edge of pan). Next, add pecans on top of coconut.
Mix boxed cake according to directions; pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix the butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar; spoon over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tangy fruit punch
directions: Place 1/2 c. water with bananas & strawberries in blender and process till smooth. Stir in rest of ingredients except ginger ale. Refrigerate and serve with ginger ale.

title: creme-de-menthe dessert
directions: Melt marshmallows with 1/4 cup milk in double boiler.
Let cool.
Add creme-de-menthe and heavy cream.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Add milk, butter, sugar and cocoa.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Take off stove and add oats, vanilla and salt.

title: farm-style beef sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and stuff into casing. Great baked, broiled or fried.

title: gourmet sirloin tips
directions: Saute garlic in hot oil.
Add meat and brown on all sides over medium heat.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to meat.
Cover and simmer over low heat on top of range or bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serve over hot fluffy rice. Serves 4.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and sprinkle additional Parmesan on top.
Bake for 1/2 hour or until hot and brown on top at 350°.
Serve with French bread.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Spray an 8 x 8 casserole dish with cooking spray. Combine the first 6 ingredients with 1 cup of Swiss cheese. Place slices of French bread over mixture and sprinkle with parsley. Bake, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add the flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Roll into small balls.
Press with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Brown chicken in hot oil on all sides.
Set aside and continue cooking until all pieces are done.
As last of chicken browns, add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for 40 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Add sherry, if desired.
Serve with pasta and a salad.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Serves 4 people.
Coat a medium saucepan with cooking spray. Melt butter over medium heat.
Add noodles constantly stirring over low heat until noodles become golden brown.
Add rice.
Coat with butter.
Meanwhile bring water or broth to a full boil.
Add at once to rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put on a tight fitting lid and simmer until water is absorbed.
If brown rice is used, add more water and cook longer.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, celery salt and garlic powder.
Shape into balls and pour remaining ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: spinach and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and spinach in water until completely thawed (but not cooked).
Stir in remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in large casserole dish and cover with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 12 servings of 1/2 cup at approximately 85 calories per serving.

title: tomato-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Stir in tomatoes, onions, garlic, parsley, oil, salt, basil and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours or until chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage pitas
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; add vegetables.
Cook until just tender.
Lightly toast pita bread.
Use spoon to open while warm. Fill with sausage and vegetables.

title: cranberry-pear relish
directions: Heat all ingredients, except liqueur, in a large saucepan to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens, about 45 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in liqueur.
Refrigerate, covered, 4 hours or overnight.
Serve slightly chilled.
Yields 8 cups.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter well.
Reserve 2/3 cup of this batter.
Spread the rest into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put corn in large bowl.
Mix sugar, water, syrup, salt and butter in saucepan.
Cook to 250° or until a few drops form a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and pour in thin stream over corn, stirring constantly to mix well.
With buttered hands, shape into balls.
Add food coloring to syrup if desired.
Makes 12 to 15 large balls.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Serve next day chilled.

title: chocolate temptation
directions: Bake brownie mix according to directions on box, adding the pecans.
After they are baked, remove from oven and crumble into crumbs.
Mix chocolate pudding according to directions on box. Place a layer of brownie crumbs in bottom of trifle bowl, then a layer of Cool Whip.
Continue until you have used all ingredients. It is best when it sits for several hours.

title: chinese vermicelli
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together sesame oil, soy sauce, sugar, chili oil and vinegar.
Cook vermicelli in boiling water until barely tender (probably less than a minute).
Drain, rinse with cold water and drain again.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and place in saucepan and place on heat. Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
This is very hot, so use pepper as you desire.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Saute 1/2 cup chopped
onion
and
1/2 cup celery until limp. Add Velveeta cheese.
Parboil
frozen spinach and drain thoroughly.
Add spinach, cream
of mushroom soup and half the bread crumbs to the pan;
blend
thoroughly.
Put
this
in
a baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining
bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger-tater tot casserole
directions: Spread hamburger in bottom of a square baking dish.
Cover with chopped onions; top with Tater Tots.
Spread Cheddar cheese soup on top.
(If you mix a little milk with the soup, it spreads much easier.)
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: triple tasty fudge bars
directions: Prepare frosting mix.
Combine dry cake mix and 1/2 of prepared frosting, water and egg; stir by hand (stiff).
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan, greased on bottom only.
Combine sour cream and remaining frosting mix and spread over mixture in pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Chop eggs; add to other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: broccoli with sesame dressing
directions: Cook spinach and broccoli as directed.
Drain well.
Mix rest of ingredients, except onion rings, with vegetables.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Add 1/2 can of onion rings.
Mix well and add rest of can on top of casserole.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat out like a hamburger and fry in butter and oil until brown.
Good with pintos or green beans.

title: sunday morning beef stew
directions: Lightly spray casserole dish with Pam.
Do not brown or salt meat.
Put meat in dish.
Pepper to taste.
Cover with chopped onion.
Mix both soups and mushrooms with juice in bowl.
Spread soup mixture over meat and onions.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 3 hours or at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: turkey breast with sherry
directions: Remove turkey breast from package.
Blot dry, using paper towels.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; dust turkey slices with seasoned flour.
Add 2 tablespoons butter in heavy skillet over medium-high heat; brown flour dusted turkey slices about 2 minutes on each side.
Remove to warm platter.
Add remaining butter and almonds, if used, to the pan.
Brown almonds over medium-high heat and turn almonds out onto platter with turkey breasts.
Add sherry to pan.
Bring to a boil and scrape pan to bring up brownings. Add cream; boil for 2 minutes.
Pour sherry-cream over turkey breasts.
Serve immediately.

title: foolproof white candy
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt white chocolate with milk.
Remove from heat; stir in salt, vanilla, cherries for color and walnuts. Spread evenly onto wax paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Pull off wax paper and cut into squares.
(Store at room temperature.)

title: hearty tuna soup
directions: Combine water or broth with contents of potato mix, including seasoning packet.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tuna, milk, broccoli and salt.
Heat 5 to 10 minutes more, until mixture is heated through.
Makes 5 servings, each with 196 calories, 4 grams fat and 15 milligrams cholesterol.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion, peas and water chestnuts in that order.
Cover with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with sugar, Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.
Add tomato wedges.
Cover and store overnight.

title: caramel-apple dessert
directions: Microwave Directions: Toss apples with 1/4 cup wheat germ and flour.
Layer apple mixture, ice cream topping and raisins in 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Microwave at High 6 to 7 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Separate crescent rolls into 2 rectangles.
Stretch dough over apples to edge of dish.
Drizzle with margarine; sprinkle with combined remaining 1/4 cup wheat germ and cinnamon.
Microwave at High 6 to 7 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Let stand on countertop for 3 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix well and place in graham cracker crust.
Chill thoroughly.

title: tabooly (suff-soof)
directions: Clean and wash vegetables and chop fine. Wash and soak wheat 10 minutes. Squeeze water from wheat and add vegetables. Add lemon juice, oil, salt and pepper and mix well. Serve with lettuce, grape leaves or cooked cabbage leaves.

title: crab chowder
directions: In 3 to 4 quart saucepan combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling; remove from heat.

title: chicken and crab meat dressing
directions: Combine 1/2 stick of melted margarine and catsup; split chicken breasts just enough to fold.
Salt and pepper.
Brush each piece with the mixture.
Place the pieces of chicken in a shallow baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, turning and basting occasionally with the mixture.

title: birthday and special occasion cake frosting
directions: Beat until smooth.
Use for frosting and decorating.
Half will do a sheet cake.

title: old-fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt in heavy saucepan.
Whisk to remove lumps.
Gradually whisk in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat the egg yolks until thick.
Stir 1/4 of the hot mixture into the yolks.
Add remaining yolks to hot mixture.
Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the butter and vanilla.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine celery, onion, eggs, chicken broth and mushroom soup. Add chicken and mix.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stromboli
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef and drain well.
In same Dutch oven, saute onion and musheroms with garlic and pepper.
Stir in meat and spaghetti sauce.
Heat until bubbly.
Spread meat mixture over both halves of Italian bread and top with cheese.
Broil 6 inches under low flame for 10 minutes.

title: classic shortbread
directions: Cream butter until light.
Mix in powdered sugar, then vanilla. Work in the flour.
Knead dough on unfloured surface until smooth. Use a shortbread pan or jelly roll pan.
Spray lightly with nonstick spray.
Put ball of dough in the middle of pan and spread to sides.
Prick entire surface with a fork, then bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes until very lightly browned.
Be sure middle of shortbread is completely cooked.
Cool 10 minutes, then loosen with a knife and flip onto a cutting board.
Cut while still warm into desired shapes.
Top with Lemon Curd, jelly or jam or dip in chocolate.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs until frothy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.

title: potato puffs
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add potatoes.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into potato mixture.
In large saucepan or kettle, heat about 1-inch of oil to 375°.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls, 4 or 5 at a time, into hot oil.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, turning once, or until golden brown.
Watch closely, since they brown quickly.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice in 4 cups of water for about 45 minutes; drain. Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix all soups together.
Blend all ingredients.
Season to taste (lemon pepper, parsley flakes, garlic powder, salt and pepper are what I use). Put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips or cornflakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: In an 8 x 12-inch baking dish, layer the rhubarb, sugar, dry gelatin and dry cake mix in that order.
Pour water over all and scatter the pieces of oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until cake is lightly browned.

title: roasted turnips, onions and carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine turnips, carrots, onions and 8 whole garlic cloves in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Drizzle vegetables with 3 tablespoons of olive oil.
Sprinkle with savory. Season with salt and pepper and toss well.
Bake until vegetables are almost tender, about 45 minutes.

title: roast turkey and cornbread stuffing
directions: Rinse turkey and wipe dry; rub with oil, then salt and pepper. In a large bowl, combine stuffing mix with oil and vegetables; stir in broth.
Mix lightly.
Stuff loosely into neck and body cavities.
Skewer neck skin to back; tuck legs under skin band. Twist wings under turkey.
Place turkey breast-side up on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Place a tent of foil over turkey. Roast at 325° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours (180° to 185° on meat thermometer).
Remove foil last 1/2 hour.
Cornbread stuffing can be cooked separately, the last 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil until fluffy.
Add pumpkin and mix. Add dry ingredients and mix . Add water and mix.
Line bottom of pan with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: dad's meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients together using 10 oz. of A-1 steak sauce. Pack into a loaf pan and top with remaining A-1 sauce. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken, rice casserole
directions: Grease bottom of casserole dish with butter.
Mix soups and rice together.
Pour in dish.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Place on top of soup mixture.
Put pat of butter on each piece.
Cook at 250° for two and one half hours. Make sure all rice is covered to prevent drying.
I cover mine with tinfoil.

title: caramel nut crunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.

Butter jelly roll pan (15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch). Heat brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and nuts until well coated. Spread in pan and bake 15 minutes. Cool until slightly firm, 5 to 7 minutes.
Loosen with metal spatula.
Let stand until firm, about 1 hour.
Makes 8 cups.

title: peanut butter holiday creams
directions: A candy thermometer is necessary for this recipe.

title: gilge christmas candy
directions: Thoroughly
mix
margarine,
sweetened
condensed milk, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Divide and add desired flavorings and colorings.
Roll into little balls.
If balls are too soft to handle, freeze them.
Then coat with melted chocolate.

title: spicy peanut dip
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients until smooth. Chill for 1 hour.
For dipping, serve with assorted fresh or blanched vegetables and pickled baby corn.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: slaw
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl.
Let set a couple hours before serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; gradually add milk until smooth. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick. Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat. Stir small amount of hot liquid into egg yolks. Return all back to pan. Bring to gentle boil, stirring constantly. Cook 20 minutes longer. (Mixture will be very thick.) Add butter and lemon peel. Gently stir in lemon juice. Cover and cool completely. Fold in sour cream; pour into pie shell. Refrigerate 2 hours. Top with Cool Whip.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Grease square baking dish.
Spread mustard on one side of each slice of rye bread.
Cut bread in 1/2-inch cubes.
Scatter over bottom of dish.
Crumble corned beef over bread.
In large bowl, mix sauerkraut, soup, water and relish until blended.
Spoon over corned beef.
Cover with microwave paper.
Microwave on High about 8 minutes (turning twice).
Place cheese on top and warm until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes, then serve.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix together all but the cheese.
Form into patties.
Fry in oil until nicely browned.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when done.

title: classic german chocolate cake
directions: In small saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate in water; stir.
In large bowl, beat sugar and shortening until fluffy. Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to batter alternately with buttermilk until blended.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Combine remaining ingredients. Mix until well blended. Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 55 minutes. Cool on rack before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In double boiler, over boiling water, dissolve cornstarch in water; stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Arrange 2 bananas on bottom of prepared pastry shell.
Pour filling over bananas; cover.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Spread top with whipping cream that you have whipped and add sugar and vanilla; garnish with remaining banana slices.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Let cool, peel and cut lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Combine next 6 ingredients in a small saucepan; stir in pineapple juice, syrup, orange juice and margarine.
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: african chop suey
directions: Brown meat; add onions, celery, soups, water, mushrooms, molasses, rice, salt and pepper.
Bake 2 hours, uncovered, at 325°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In a casserole dish, melt stick of margarine in a 375° oven; in same dish, add the remaining ingredients and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with ice cream.
Fast and easy dessert!

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and jello.
Add pineapple; mix, then add marshmallows.
Let set for a few hours before eating.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and onion and green pepper (optional).
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep 2 weeks or more.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add orange jello. Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and let stand until almost congealed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add Cheddar cheese and nuts.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Measure
flour;
add
baking powder, salt, baking soda, sugar and
spices.
Combine
eggs
and
oil.
Pour into flour mixture, stirring just enough to moisten the dry ingredients. Add pumpkin and vanilla, mixing well.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon batter
into greased or paper-lined medium-sized muffin pans, filling each
cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or
until
a
wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Makes about 18 muffins.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix together and pour into funnel.
Release and make circles of batter into hot grease.
Cook 10 to 15 seconds on each side. Dust with powdered sugar while still hot when placed on plate. Makes 10 (5-inch) cakes.

title: spinach puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill in covered dish for 2 or more hours.
Roll or shape into balls about the size of walnuts. Freeze or refrigerate until ready to use.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Makes 60.

title: fresh-as-spring salad
directions: Cut 6 asparagus spears into 4 inch lengths and marinate with cherry
tomato halves in 2 tablespoons Italian dressing; cover and refrigerate.
Cut remaining asparagus into 1/2 inch pieces; reserve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease tube pan.
Cut roll dough pieces in half (while still mostly frozen) and place in pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over dough pieces and sprinkle nuts and cinnamon over brown sugar.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Cover with a tea towel and leave on countertop overnight.
In morning, heat oven to 350°.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until browned and done.
Invert on a plate and remove pan.

title: hot cheese sandwiches
directions: Soften cheese and margarine.
Mix with the other ingredients. Spread cheese mixture on bread.
Layer into 3 layers.
Cut into thirds, finger size.
Seal each slice with cheese mixture (like icing on a cake).
This is messy!
Place on a cookie sheet and quick freeze.
After they harden, place in plastic bags in the freezer.

title: wild grape dumplings
directions: Stir listed items together to form stiff dough.
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons more juice if needed.

title: ginger chicken wings
directions: Mix well and pour over wings.
Refrigerate and marinate for 3 to 5 hours.
Broil and add a little sauce at a time.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until crisp.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and melted oleo.
Use about 2/3 of it to line the bottom of a casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream, grated onion and carrots.
Stir in remaining vegetables and place over stuffing layer.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture on top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: In large skillet quickly brown chops in oil; drain fat. Combine pineapple chunks and juice with ketchup.
Add onion, salt and pepper and pour over chops.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Turn chops.
Add green pepper cut into chunks.
Cover; cook another 15 minutes.
Thicken sauce with cornstarch and water.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese if desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into baking dish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Turn off heat and add dash of salt, vanilla, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut when cool.

title: coconut orange balls
directions: Mix well crushed vanilla wafers, sugar and nuts.
Add orange juice and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Form into small balls and roll in coconut.
Store in a cool place.
Yields:

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Add tomato paste, stirring constantly.
When mixed well, pour into very large pot and add crushed tomatoes, oregano, basil, parsley and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 2 hours and 45 minutes.
Add sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Continue to simmer for 15 minutes.
Let cool and store extra sauce in freezer.
Makes a lot!

title: tailgate pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Press crescent rolls out on a jelly roll pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes. Cool. Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and dip mix.
Spread over cooled rolls.
Top with finely chopped vegetables, then top with grated cheese. Cut in squares and serve as an appetizer.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Drain.
Add Manwich to meat mixture.
Mix up cornbread in bowl.
Spread 1/2 in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour meat mixture on top.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake until brown.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Divide batter.
Place in two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake at 450°.
Yields two 9 x 13-inch pans.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Put oil and flour in pot.
Slowly brown flour, stirring constantly (flour should be very dark, but not burned).
Add onions, celery, parsley and garlic, lightly saute.
Add tomato paste, 5 cups water and other seasonings.
Cook for 3 hours on very low temperature.
Add raw shrimp.
Cook 30 minutes before serving.
Just before serving, add eggs.
Serve over hot rice.

title: frozen daiquiris drink
directions: Mix all
together;
put in freezer.
If you wish to put in fresh
strawberries, put strawberries into blender; strain and add juice to the mixture.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls.
Bake in 400° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey a la king
directions: Mix dressing according to directions.
Add raisins and celery. Press in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken, mushrooms and three soups and put on top of dressing.
Crush crackers.
Mix cheese and butter into crackers.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over hot dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Take off foil for last 15 minutes.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef; add salt, pepper and any other spices to taste.
Drain.
Blend together next 5 ingredients.
Place beef in pie shell.
Pour milk and mayonnaise mixture over meat.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chile rellenos
directions: Layer cheese and chiles.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over layers.
Cover and let stand one hour.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until slightly firm.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: s'more supreme(for kids)
directions: Place 4 graham cracker halves on your work surface.
Spread the first cracker with 1/4 of the softened ice cream.
Top with 2 tablespoons of Marshmallow Fluff.
Drizzle with 1 1/2 teaspoons of the chocolate syrup and place a cracker over the top.
Freeze first S'more while you work on others.
Repeat until finished.
Serve soon or graham cracker will crumble.

title: corn souffle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in a large bowl; add both kinds corn, cornbread mix, sour cream and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 minutes.

title: party hors d'oeuvres(also diabetic)
directions: Cream all ingredients; roll in chopped nuts or celery.
Shape into a ball.
Chill.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix yeast, water, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add flour; mix well.
Put dough on wax paper; knead until smooth.
Cut pieces and make into shapes, not too thick, not too thin.
Put on cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg; sprinkle them with coarse salt. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: good sweet and sour pork
directions: In large skillet, brown pork.
Add water; cover and simmer until tender (1 hour).
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Mix pineapple syrup, brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Cook over medium heat until thickens.
Cook pineapple, bell pepper and onion in small amount of oil or butter until tender; add to pork mixture.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients in order.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hazel's christmas pickles
directions: Fill a one gallon glass jar with small to medium cucumbers which have been thoroughly washed.
Add all the preceding ingredients and finish filling the jar with water.
Put lid on and shake well, let stand in cool place till December, (standing longer will not affect quality).
Open jar; drain and wash pickles.
Cut into bite size chunks and put back into jar.
Dissolve 7 cups of sugar in a quart of water and pour over cucumbers.
If necessary, add more water to cover pickles; let stand for 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: courtney's easy-cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, bone it and cube meat.
Boil broth in saucepan, stir in flour to thicken, add cheese and let melt.
Add noodles and chicken.
Pour into casserole.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top.
Pour evaporated milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 30- minutes.
(May be made ahead and baked when ready.)

title: potato salad
directions: Cook peeled Irish potatoes in pan of water until just tender. While potatoes are cooking, chop onion, bell pepper, boiled eggs and sweet pickle in bowl.
Drain potatoes and pour into onion mix. Add salad dressing and salt and pepper to taste.

title: peggy's scalloped potatoes
directions: Cut skinned potatoes into thin slices.
Pour soup and milk over layered potatoes in a deep baking dish.
Place dabs of butter and bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(Cover pan with foil.)

title: orange slice cake
directions: In a separate large pan, add chopped dates, orange slices, nuts, salt and flour.
Melt margarine and cream in sugar; add eggs and 1 cup of buttermilk.
Add soda to remaining 1/2 cup of buttermilk and add to mixture of oranges, dates, flour, nuts and salt.
Mix well with hands.
Bake in tube cake pan for 3 or 4 hours at 275°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done; debone and shred. Cook spaghetti in remaining broth. Saute pepper and onion in butter. Mix spaghetti and soup with cheese. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Bake in buttered casserole dish at 350° until bubbly.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Fill blender container to top-cup marking with vegetables. Add cold water just to cover vegetables.
Cover container; follow manufacturer's instructions or run just long enough to chop vegetables, about 3 to 4 seconds.
Pour mixture into strainer; drain thoroughly.
Repeat with remaining vegetables.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown the meat; add onions and cook a few minutes.
Add soup, sauerkraut and rice.
Bake covered 1 hour at 300°, then 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Serve with rye bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, carrots, onion, sour cream and cheese. Add stuffing mix to butter. Grease dish with butter. Spread small amount of stuffing mixture on bottom of dish. Pour squash into dish and top with remaining stuffing mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and let cool to touch.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup butter and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Gently stir in potatoes and cheese.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken and then shred. Add chicken and 1/2 of each of the ingredients and roll into tortillas.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring cranberries, sugar and water to a rolling boil.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
(To make sweeter, you may substitute strawberry jello instead of cherry.)
When mixture is cool, add celery, nuts and apples.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 12 baking pan.
Let set.
Serve by cutting into squares.
Enjoy!

title: meat and vegetable stew
directions: In a nonstick pot, put enough oil to coat bottom of pot. Dredge meat in flour with salt and pepper.
Heat oil and add meat. Cook until brown. Add any leftover flour to pot.
Stir in onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic. Cover and lower heat to simmer. Cook 1/2 hour. Add water, carrots, potatoes, salt and pepper. Cook slowly 1 hour.
Adjust seasoning. Serve over cooked rice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and crumble sausage (hot or mild; we prefer the hot); drain and cool.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and milk together with beater a couple of minutes.
Add salt and mustard and beat again. Trim crust off white bread and break into small pieces.
Add bread to egg mixture and stir until softened.
Stir in cheese, mushrooms and sausage.
Pour into a greased (with butter) 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° uncovered for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.
Great luncheon dish as well!

title: carrot cake muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin tins with paper baking cups or spray bottoms with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine dry ingredients and raisins.
Add combined remaining ingredients mixed just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups almost full; lightly sprinkle with additional wheat germ, if desired.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 low-fat muffins.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine and bake 15 minutes at 425°, then 45 minutes at 350°.

title: scallop puffs
directions: Slice French bread in thin slices.
Set aside.
Saute scallops, lemon zest and garlic in butter, then add dill.
Let cool.
Add Swiss cheese and mayo.
Place on slices of French bread.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 to 25 minutes until puffed and golden brown.

title: chili cheese rounds
directions: Cream softened oleo and cheese.
Blend in flour and chili powder.
Work it with hands and shape into small balls; press on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Combine all
ingredients and put half of the mixture in the bottom of
a
x	13-inch
pan.
Place chicken pieces on rice. Add
balance
of
rice mixture.
Parmesan cheese and/or Mozzarella cheese may	be
added.
Bake
1/2 hours at 250°, uncovered. May be baked 1 hour at 375°.
(I prefer the slower cooking.)

title: chocolate shot cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually; cream until fluffy.
Add vanilla and flour with soda mixed in; add oatmeal.
Chill 30 minutes and then roll dough in log shape.
Then roll log in chocolate decors or shots.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake on foil covered cookie sheet at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: florida pies
directions: Mix the fruit and nuts together and drain.
Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together.
Stir fruit into milk mixture and pour in pie shells.
Refrigerate overnight or 4 to 6 hours.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: slushy fruit punch
directions: Process sugar, water, sherbet, bananas, pineapple juice, orange juice, Hawaiian punch and lemon juice about 1/3 at a time in blender.
Pour into 1 large or several small freezer containers.
Freeze until firm.
Let large container stand at room temperature for 1 hour or smaller containers for 30 minutes or until slushy; do not thaw completely.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add lemon-lime soda to slush mixture just before serving.
Garnish with fresh fruit of choice.

title: taco casserole
directions: Break taco shells or Doritos in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add taco mix as directed. Add beans and simmer.
Pour over chips.
Top with grated cheese.
Put in a 325° oven just until cheese is melted.
Serve with layered salad.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Put in greased casserole.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing and bake 20 minutes at 325° or until brown on top.
Good with Ritz crackers.

title: rib-ticklin' barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, stir together all ingredients.
Stirring frequently, bring to a boil; reduce heat and boil gently 15 minutes to thicken.
Brush on meat, turning frequently during last 20 minutes of cooking.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the hash browns, soup, sour cream, 3/4 of the melted margarine, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch glass Pyrex dish.
Mix the remaining margarine with the corn flakes and top the hash brown mixture.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh cranberry orange relish
directions: Slice unpeeled orange into eighths.
Remove seeds.
Place half the cranberries and half the orange slices in food processor container.
Process until mixture is evenly chopped.
Transfer to a bowl.
Repeat with remaining cranberries and orange slices. Stir in sugar to desired sweetness.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: carolina christmas cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add well beaten egg and applesauce (Use a little of the flour to dredge fruit and nuts).
Sift remaining flour mixture alternately with the water to the creamed mixture.
Add flour, raisins and nuts.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Mix next 10 ingredients together.
Stuff into cooked manicotti.
Place into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan into which 1/2 of the sauce has been poured.
Pour remaining sauce over the manicotti.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Can be made ahead, freezes well before or after baking.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda & salt. Set aside.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix margarine, 3 cups flour, vanilla, water, sugar, eggs and lemon extract to make batter.
Dredge fruit, nuts, raisins and coconut in 1 cup flour.
Add to batter mix.
Put into Bundt pan. Put pan of water in oven on shelf under cake.
Cook 1 hour at 325°, then remove water from oven.
Continue to cook cake until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and slowly add chicken broth. Cook and stir until thick.
Stir in milk, sherry, salt and pepper. Gradually add cheese.
Stir in cooked chicken cubes and peas. Serve over rice.
Makes 2 1/4 cups gravy.

title: cocktail franks
directions: In a saucepan, combine equal portions of mustard and jelly. Heat slowly on low heat until jelly melts and sauce becomes smooth and well blended.
Remove strings from franks and place in sauce. Heat 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Let the cream cheese soften. Mix the soften cheese together with the pineapple, onions, and ham. Form into a ball. Roll in the nuts to coat the cheese ball. Place on an attractive serving dish, place in the refrigerator until it is well chilled and serve with party crackers.

title: salmon bits
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Break meat apart.
Add flour and slightly beaten egg.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add baking powder to liquid; beat until foamy.
Pour into salmon mixture.
Drop by teaspoon in deep fryer half full of oil.
Remove from oil as soon as brown.
These are very crisp and light.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in jam and preserves.
Stir together all dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk to jam mixture. Bake for 40 minutes in 3 well-greased cake pans or Bundt pan. Cool for 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix together and freeze and keep frozen.
Use ice cream scoop and fill glass 3/4 full.
Add 7-Up and stir.
Add cherry.
This will keep frozen for a long time.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Put tomato soup in 2 quart saucepan and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and add gelatine and stir for 4 minutes.
Add cream cheese and stir until smooth.
Take off heat.
Fold in mayonnaise, celery, onion and shrimp.
Put into a 4 cup mold and chill overnight.

title: beef, bean and cornbread casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in a large saucepan coated with cooking spray over medium-high heat until browned, stirring frequently to crumble the beef.
Drain the beef mixture in a colander.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and butter.
Add pecans, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes one pie.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and flour.
Beat until creamy.
Add corn syrup, butter and extract.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: refrigerator confetti brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine crumbs, marshmallows, nuts and sugar. In a saucepan, melt chocolate chips and milk over low heat, stirring often until blended smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add extract, if desired.
Set aside 1/2 cup.
Pour remaining chocolate mix over crumb mix; mix until well blended.
Pour batter onto greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Press down evenly.
Frost with reserved chocolate mixture.
Chill for an hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift flour and other dry ingredients. Combine egg, milk and oil. Mix together and fry on pancake griddle.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cover chicken with water, salt and pepper and cook until done. Take chicken out of broth to cool.
Chop potatoes, onion and celery.
Add to the chicken broth along with the corn.
Add crushed pepper flakes.
Cook until done.
Pick chicken off bones and add to soup.
This can be used as is or thicken with rice, noodles or rivels.
If you use any of these, cook again until done.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Chill overnight, or until you can roll into ball.
Roll in crushed nuts or parsley.

title: cranberry ice
directions: Boil cranberries in cold water until mushy.
Put through sieve. Add sugar and cook on low heat until sugar dissolves.
Add orange juice and rind.
Put in freezer until hard.
Remove and beat until frothy.
Refreeze.
Serve with a turkey dinner.
A holiday tradition.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp, eggs and milk. Sift dry ingredients together and add to pulp mixture.
Pour into greased pan to depth of 2-inches. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: rocky road
directions: Place chocolate
morsels,
milk
and
butter in top of a double boiler;
bring
to
a
boil.
Reduce
heat to low;
cook until
chocolate and butter melts, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, and stir in pecans and marshmallows.
Spread mixture into a waxed
paper lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch squares, store in refrigerator.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Chop green peppers and onions.
Cut zucchini lengthwise into 1/4's; cut each 1/4 crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk.
Spread on top of cool pie crust.
Slice half of the strawberries on top of the cream cheese mixture. Cook the other half of the strawberries, cornstarch and lemon juice until it thickens.
When cool, spread on top.

title: australian sultana loaf
directions: In bowl, beat potatoes with the sugar.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine with potato mixture.
Stir in the raisins, then add milk and spices.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased loaf tin.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Allow to cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.

title: low calorie beef and potato casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
