Arrange diced potatoes in bottom and sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon crumbled oregano, 1/4 teaspoon salt and some freshly ground pepper.
Crumble ground chuck over potatoes in an even layer.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon more oregano, 1/4 teaspoon salt and some more pepper.

title: grandma honey's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls the size of quarters. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar. Yields 36 cookies.

title: apple ring cucumber pickles
directions: Slice, peel and cut centers out of cucumbers.
Soak overnight in lime water.
Drain and soak overnight in ice water; leave in icebox the next day for 4 hours.
Next, mix sugar, vinegar, alum, salt, red hots, food coloring and cinnamon sticks; bring to boil. Reduce heat and boil gently for 30 minutes.
Can in jars.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 of margarine and cream cheese with hot spinach.
Add egg; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch dish.
Mix rest of margarine (melted) with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Simmer sauce and grape jelly while meatballs are baking.
Use crock-pot.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and marinate chicken breasts overnight. Roll chicken breasts in bread crumbs and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes in foil covered pan at 325°.
Open foil for last few minutes of baking time.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Blend in remaining ingredients, adding more milk if mixture is too thick. Sprinkle additional cornmeal on bottom of hot greased iron skillet. Bake in preheated 450° oven 20 minutes or until brown.

title: stir and bake bars
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add the water and eggs and mix until well blended.
Spread in a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts combined with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting in squares.

title: impossible coconut pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place drained pineapple in casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour and sprinkle on top of pineapple.
Add grated cheese followed by crushed crackers.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.
Serve warm.

title: olga's pound cake
directions: In
measuring
cup,
break
in eggs plus enough milk to make 1 cup. In mixing bowl, cream shortening with sugar.
Beat eggs with milk slightly and add to shortening and sugar.
Sift flour
and salt together.
Add baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture
and mix until all is well mixed at a low speed.
Then add
cup milk,
some
lemon
rind or vanilla.
Mix for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion and water in saucepan.

Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until squash is tender. Drain and mash. Combine squash, cheese, pecans, green peppers, mayonnaise, egg, salt, sugar and pepper, stirring well. Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole. Combine cracker crumbs and butter, stirring well. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: goofy bars
directions: Place dry cake mix in a bowl.
Put eggs in measuring cup and add enough water to make 2/3 cup.
Add to brown sugar and beat until well blended. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chips and marshmallows on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ashton's sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except walnuts, in greased casserole. Sprinkle nuts around outside edges. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator to warm. Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cracker crumbs and 4 tablespoons butter; press into 8-inch pie plate.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter. Saute onions until tender.
Beat other ingredients, except cheese, together.
Pour onions over cracker crust. Pour other mixture over onions.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and dot with paprika or parsley flakes.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add sugar, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Mix cocoa and water together.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken chili bake
directions: Combine rice and chicken broth in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 50 minutes or until rice is tender and moisture is absorbed.
Combine chicken and remaining ingredients in a large bowl; stir in rice.
Spoon mixture into a 2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: eggplant genovese
directions: Mix the tomato paste with an equal amount of water.
Add herbs, salt and sugar; simmer on low heat to a boil.
Cut the eggplant in one-inch slices, lengthwise.
Pour oil in casserole and alternate layers of eggplant slices with cheese, finishing with the cheese.
Pour the tomato sauce over it and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll out dough on well floured towel to about 1/4-inch deep. Cut with doughnut cutter or in strips, if desired. Fry in deep fryer until golden brown. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Wash, cut up and partially cook broccoli.
Drain.
Add garlic cheese, almonds, margarine, onion, soup, mushrooms, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with sage, if desired.
Cooking time is about 10 minutes.

title: clam cakes
directions: Mix in order given and fry in deep fat.
It is extremely important that you mix the ingredients in the order given or the results will not be as good.

title: rice and beef casserole
directions: Cook beef until brown.
Drain and add remaining ingredients. Bake for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: heavenly biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let set until completely dissolved, stirring occasionally.
Add to Bisquick.
Stir vigorously 2 minutes.
Pour onto a floured sheet of wax or plastic wrap.
Knead until smooth.
Cover with mixing bowl and let rest 10 to 15 minutes.
Press down and cut out biscuits with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place in a greased baking dish and let rise for at least 30 minutes.
If using a glass baking dish, bake for 18 minutes at 425°.
Yields 15 biscuits.
Brush with butter after baked.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan.
Grate zucchini and chop onion.
Beat eggs.
Add oil and Bisquick; blend thoroughly. To this mixture, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave green bean casserole
directions: Mix milk and soup.
Microwave on high 2 minutes.
Stir.
Add green beans.
Microwave on high 2-3 minutes.
Add onions and almonds.
Microwave on high another 2-3 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and dust with flour a 17 1/4 x 11 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
In a medium mixing bowl, beat eggs for 5 minutes on medium speed.
Add all other ingredients one at a time, in any order, mixing well after each addition, until entire mixture is creamy smooth.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Blend cheese, butter and margarine well in mixer.
Add sugar. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and flour alternately (mix as follows:
one egg, 1/2 cup flour, continue).
Blend well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Start cake in cold oven.
Turn oven to 300° and bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.
Remove from pan immediately.
Cake stays fresh over a week and freezes well.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Gently wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Finely dice stems; set aside.
Place mushroom caps, open end up, in a large flat casserole.
Melt approximately 1/2 of the stick of the butter. Add the onion and mushroom caps.
Lightly saute until golden. Remove from heat; add the diced pepperoni and bread crumbs, mixing well.
(I usually use 1 cup of crumbs first to see how well the mixture holds together.
If I need more, I use more.)
Stir in the shredded cheese.
Stuff the mushroom caps; drizzle with the remaining melted butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 to 15 minutes, or until cheese melts in topping and mushrooms are light golden brown.
You can also broil these appetizers at 425° for about 5 to 8 minutes.
Serves 16 to 25.

title: new zealand salad
directions: Mix well. Delicious poured over grapefruit sections and sliced avocado on lettuce.

title: quick cheese fondue
directions: In a 4-cup glass measure, blend soup and milk; cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Add garlic powder and nutmeg; stir to blend.
Blend in cheese.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring every minute, until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: caesar salad with sourdough croutons
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in processor or blender. With machine running, gradually add oil in thin steady stream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Prepare 1 day ahead.
Cover and chill. Bring to room temperature before serving.
Combine lettuce, onion and croutons in a large bowl. Toss with enough dressing to season to taste.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eyes of texas salad
directions: Combine cooled black-eyed peas, rice and chicken.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well and pack into an oiled 5 1/2 cup mold.
Refrigerate until set.
Unmold and spread with Avocado Topping.
(Don't like molds?
Just use a casserole dish.)

title: orange apricot salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Let set. Once congealed top with cool whip and marshmallows. Sprinkle shredded cheddar cheese over marshmallows.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze water from spinach.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly and chill for 1 hour.
Nice when served with sliced pumpernickel!

title: brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Separately combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add egg mixture. Bake in greased and floured 12 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: viva la chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in foil.
Bake for 1 hour in 400° oven.
Cook and save juice.
Bone and cut in large pieces.
Cut the tortillas in 1-inch strips.
Grease bottom and sides of oblong Pyrex casserole dish.
Put the round sides of tortillas around the edge of the dish.
Put half of the strips on the bottom.
Mix together soups, milk, onion and salsa.
Pour juice from chicken in bottom of dish.
Put half of chicken pieces over the bottom, then half of the sauce.
Repeat the layers, starting with tortilla strips.
Put cheese on top.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bake 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.

title: pork chop delight
directions: To large casserole dish, add cooked potatoes, cooked carrots and frozen broccoli.
Cover with margarine, parsley and onions. Top this with pork chops.
Pour onion soup mix and water over pork chops.
Cover with foil and bake for 2 hours at 400°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well; chill and serve.
You can substitute peach pie filling for apricot pie filling and can of apricots for can of peaches.
You can top with Cool Whip, if desired.
Salad will last longer without bananas in it.

title: wiener-bean pot
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish combine undrained tomatoes (chopped), mushrooms (optional) and 4 tablespoons Village Saucerie.
Place chicken over sauce mixture. Sprinkle remaining 2 tablespoons Village Saucerie over chicken; spread evenly.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle chicken with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Cool. Baste meat.

title: low calorie pineapple cheesecake
directions: Blend together first two ingredients in a blender.
Then add the next four ingredients and blend until smooth.
Then fold in last 2 ingredients and pour into large baking dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup of the cheese and croutons.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with reserved 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Bake for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add garlic, onion, green pepper and zucchini.
Cook about 3 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring frequently.
Add eggplant and spices; cover and cook over medium heat 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook 5 minutes longer or until tomatoes are heated.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Cook sausage
and
drain.
Roll
out biscuits until you have one huge
round.
Spread sausage over it and roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut	into
1/2-inch rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together.
Add the molasses mixture and beaten egg.
Sift the flour with the other spices and baking powder, add to the creamed mixture alternately with cold water and soda mixture.
Roll out and cut the cookies into round shapes or place by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet and press down with the base of a glass covered with flour (quicker).
Sprinkle with sugar and top with a walnut or pecan.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes (keep watch).

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening in mixer. Add eggs. Beat well. Add oats, flour, coconut, soda and vanilla. Blend until mixture is moistened. Drop onto greased baking sheet using #40 dipper. Bake in a 18 x 26-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned around edges. Do not overbake. Yield: 200 cookies.

title: rice krispie chicken supreme
directions: Place crushed cereal in a shallow dish; stir in paprika.
In another dish, beat egg and milk slightly.
Add flour, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Mix until smooth.

title: sarah's cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in the sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Spoon the mixture into the prepared crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: creole burgers
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions and saute.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain well if needed.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Turn heat to low and simmer covered for 30 minutes. Serve over toasted bread or hamburger buns.
Great served with a green salad.

title: marshmallow puffs
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and egg and cream well.
Add pineapple, flour, baking soda and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
When cookie is baked, put 1/2 marshmallow on each, sticky side down, while resting on oven door.
Put back in oven 1 second.
Remove and cool on cloth.
Frost cookie; dip in coconut and put cherry on top.

title: pickled okra
directions: Use first 3 ingredients for each pint jar.
Place 1/2 teaspoon dill weed in bottom of jar.
Wash okra; place in jar.
Add other 1/2 teaspoon dill.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over okra in jar.
Seal and allow to stand for 2 weeks before eating.

title: apricot jam
directions: Heat the applesauce until it's hot and bubbly.
Then turn the heat to a low setting and add the Jell-O and sugar.
Stir this mixture until the sugar and Jell-O dissolves.
Cool and place in containers.
This jam must be stored in the refrigerator.
Enjoy this jam on homemade bread or biscuits.

title: brazilian salad
directions: Combine fruit and vegetables, mix with mayonnaise and lemon juice and season.
Serve on lettuce.

title: kielbasa appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except kielbasa, in medium saucepan; stir well.
Cook over low heat 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add kielbasa and cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve warm.

title: mrs. thelma's jam cake
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar gradually; cream until light and fluffy.
Beat egg yolks; add to creamed mixture.
Sift together the soda, nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon and flour.
Combine jam and sour milk.
Add dry sifted ingredients and jam mixture to the creamed mixture.
Add raisins.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Divide the batter equally into 2 (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate nut bread
directions: Combine all wet ingredients and sugar; mix all dry ingredients together.
Add wet ingredients to dry and mix.
Add nuts and chips.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour. Make 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook chicken and cut in pieces.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Put broccoli on the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of broccoli. Put soup mixture over that.
Spread shredded cheese on top of dressing.
Sprinkle lemon juice on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mother's vegetable salad
directions: Drain veggies and mix with onion, green pepper and celery. Mix sugar, wine vinegar and oil together and pour over veggies. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute
hamburger until brown.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes and simmer
for
minutes.
Add water and bring to a boil. Add Veg-All, soup mix and orzo.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes, oregano and garlic salt.
Lower heat and simmer 1 hour.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: paintbrush cookies
directions: Mix well in bowl the sugar, shortening, honey, egg and vanilla.
Sift together in another bowl the sifted flour, soda and salt.

title: chive muffins
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl and make a well in center of mixture.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling about 2/3 full.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until muffins are lightly browned. Remove muffins from pan immediately.

title: parsnip pie
directions: Saute parsnips, leeks, onions and garlic in olive oil over medium heat; do not allow this mixture to brown.
You can mix a little butter with your olive oil if you like.
Layer mixture alternately with Parmesan cheese into crust.
Some times we mix in some sauteed spinach as well.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with sliced tomatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pizza(makes two dough crusts)
directions: Mix yeast
and
water
together.
Pour
into
flour and salt. Add 2
more
cups flour.
Grease bowl and let sit 1 1/2 to 2 hours until dough doubles in size; punch down and refrigerate for
2 hours.
Mix tomato sauce, garlic, oregano, basil, sugar and salt and
let simmer for 5 minutes.
Roll out dough and top with favorite
toppings.
Bake
at
425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey schnitzel
directions: Beat egg, milk and oil together.
Dip turkey slices in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
Place in a single layer in greased baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, turning once.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, brown and white sugar.
Add eggs, salt and chocolate (melted in boiling water).
Alternately add buttermilk and dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in layers or 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Scoop egg yolks from egg.
Mix all ingredients except paprika. Fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except candy kisses in large mixing bowl.
Mix on lowest speed of mixer until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls using 1 rounded teaspoon for each.
Roll balls in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.

title: cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add grated cheese and chopped nuts; mix well.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Batter will be lumpy.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 1 hour.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in a heavy pan.
Add butter flavoring and pecans and stir to coat pecans.
Remove from heat. Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla; mix only until blended. Do not beat.
Add chocolate-nut mixture and again mix carefully without beating.
Pour into 18 baking cups in muffin pans.
Bake at 325° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: angel food quickie
directions: Slice angel food cake in bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Layer fruit next.
Cover with one box instant vanilla pudding, mixed with 2 cups milk and 8 ounces sour cream.
Cover with carton of Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture.
Add flavoring and pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Refrigerate.

title: loretta's red rice
directions: Saute green pepper, celery and onion with sausage in a tablespoon of butter.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, 2 cans water, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil and add rice. Reduce heat. Cover and let simmer for 20 minutes or until all the liquid is absorbed.

title: mushroom bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Unroll crescent roll dough onto baking sheet and pinch together seams.
Toss sliced mushrooms in melted butter to coat.
Arrange mushrooms on top of dough. Sprinkle with cheese and Italian seasoning.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into wedges or squares with a pizza cutter and serve warm.
Makes 8 to 10 appetizer servings.

title: easy and fast pecan rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and Cool Whip and put into 9 x 13-inch spray coated baking dish.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over mixture.
Cut each biscuit into quarters and place tightly together over mixture and nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool for a few minutes before turning baking dish over onto a flat dish or cookie sheet.
Pecan rolls will drop easily onto dish or cookie sheet.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Drop noodles into 6 cups rapidly boiling water; heat to rapid boil.
Cook,
stirring constantly, 3 minutes; cover and remove from heat.	Let stand for 10 minutes; drain.
Heat oven to	350°. Stir
margarine
and onion into noodles.
Stir eggs into
sour cream.
Stir
egg
mixture,
ham, salt, pepper and caraway seed, if desired, into noodles.
Sprinkle bread crumbs evenly
in
a greased 2-quart casserole.	Pour noodle mixture into
casserole. Sprinkle
with
paprika.
Bake,
uncovered, until
mixture is set, 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve from casserole or	unmold	onto
heated platter.
To
unmold, loosen edge of noodles
around inside rim with knife.
Place inverted platter over
casserole;
invert noodles
onto platter.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Serves 4.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Cover bottom of skillet to 1/4 to 1/2-inch of oil.
Heat. Lightly salt and pepper steak pieces.
Roll steak in flour until covered.
Fry breaded steak in oil until browned on both sides. Drain well.
Put meat in gravy.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix and put in baking dish.
Mix crust up and pour on top.

title: piccadillo(pic-a-de-o)
directions: Combine all seasonings; stir with fork.
Saute onions and peppers in 2 tablespoons olive oil; set aside.
Saute meat in 2 tablespoons olive oil; stir in seasonings.
Add Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce; stir well.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and margarine for 20 minutes.
Then add lemon extract and flour.
Beat for 5 more minutes.
Then add 7-Up and beat for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate 24 hours. Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: chocolate icebox dessert
directions: Cut oleo into flour with pastry cutter.
Add nuts and cut again.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and chill.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Mix in Cool Whip and spread on pie crust.
Chill.

title: chicken divan
directions: Precook chicken and broccoli separately.
Spread broccoli in a casserole and place chicken on top.
In separate bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly cream oil, butter and both sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in and blend.
Roll teaspoon of dough into a ball; roll ball into granulated sugar.
Press down on a lightly greased cookie sheet with a glass tumbler dipped in sugar.
Bake about 12 minutes. Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: savory sirloin steak
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Combine rosemary and pepper; sprinkle over steak.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add margarine and place over medium heat until margarine melts.
Add steak and cook 6 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness.
Remove steak from skillet; transfer to a serving platter and keep warm.
Combine yogurt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated (do not boil).
Spoon sauce over warm steak. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: bisquick caramel rolls
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Roll out and spread with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll up and cut into slices.
Melt 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons margarine and add brown sugar.
Place spoonfuls of mixture in bottom of muffin cups.
Place a slice of dough in each cup.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: salsa
directions: Simmer all ingredients in large pot, uncovered, for 1 hour. Make paste of 6 tablespoons cornstarch and 2/3 cup water.
Add to sauce and simmer to thicken.

title: basic muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine the oat bran cereal, nuts, raisins and baking powder.
Stir the brown sugar or liquid sweetening.
Mix the milk, egg whites and oil together and blend in with the oat bran mixture.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick; it should come out moist but not wet.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: forever amber candy
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan for 45 minutes at 300°.
Take from oven and spoon into bowl of powdered sugar and roll.
When taken from oven, dip with 1 teaspoon and use another to roll.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Makes 2 loaves.
Put sauce on top of loaves before baking.

title: cheddar bay biscuits
directions: Preheat heat oven to 450.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat to dissolve pineapple juice and lime Jell-O.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Cream the cream cheese and Miracle Whip.
Add this to whipped cream and crushed pineapple.
Mix all together and put in a mold; chill.
Green food coloring may be added for a little more color.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease well and flour a stem cake pan. Into bowl, put butter and sugar and cream thoroughly. Add flour and eggs alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Mix thoroughly after each addition. Add vanilla last of all. Pour batter into pan and start in a cold oven. Cook 1 hour at 325°. Do not open oven door during that hour. If not quite golden brown at end of time, increase heat to 350° and allow another 5 minutes or so.

title: grandmas peach pie
directions: In a large bowl stir

the above ingredients together and transfer to nutmeg pie crust. Dot with butter and top with nutmeg pastry. Cut 12 slits in top of pastry to allow steam to escape. Cover pastry edge with foil. Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes. Remove foil and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly in the center.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice thoroughly.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into 3 prepared graham cracker shells.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
May be frozen.
May garnish with red or green cherries.
Makes 3 pies.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl; beat until smooth, using a wire whisk.
Layer half of cooked macaroni in bottom of a greased 9-inch square baking dish, sprinkle with 1 2/3 cups cheese and layer remaining macaroni on top.
Pour milk mixture over macaroni; sprinkle with breadcrumbs. Bake uncovered for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and continue baking 5 minutes longer or until set.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Pop corn.
Combine corn syrup, margarine and sugar.
Heat and bring to boiling.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir well, it will be foamy.
Pour over popcorn in a large bowl and toss or stir well. Coat a large grocery bag with Pam or any baking spray, put corn in bag.
Turn down top of bag until closed.
Microwave on power 7 for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove bag open up and shake well.
Microwave again on power level 7 for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take out and shake again.
Put in and microwave for 30 seconds longer (if it is not brown enough, place in large bowl or on wax paper.
Separate it.
Cool and store. All microwaves may vary, so don't over cook it.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix and add raisins.
Add 2 eggs, beaten.
Cook for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Mix well, then add 1 cup juice.
When partly congealed, add pineapple, celery, nut meats and cream cheese that has been creamed well.
Then fold in whipping cream.
Chill.

title: potato soup(yia yias)
directions: In 6-quart
pot, boil potatoes until tender, not mushy. Drain. Saute celery and onion in a little oil and butter; set aside. Put
potatoes
into pot; mash coarsely.
Add onion and celery. Add
hot
milk,
salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth. Stir well. If	too
thick,
add
more	milk
to thickness you desire.	We like it thick.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water with lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Chill.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat
the
butter
at medium speed with electric mixer, about 2
minutes, until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed
to
minutes.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating
just until
yellow
disappears.
Combine
flour
and baking
soda. Add
to
creamed
mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at lowest speed just
until blended
after
each addition.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°. Cool
in
pan on wire rack 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack.

title: fitas
directions: Saute meat, onions and peppers until done.
Fill shells; add tomatoes and cheese.
Wrap and pour picante sauce over them or some people like to put picante sauce inside shell.

title: mesquite grilled cajun turkey
directions: Prepare grill for indirect method.
Brush turkey with oil. Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over turkey.
Place turkey on grill.
Cover grill and cook according to package directions.
Wrap in foil and let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove netting from turkey and slice turkey.

title: white chocolate mousse with frangelico
directions: Melt the white chocolate and butter in a small saucepan, stirring constantly.
Set aside. Beat egg yolks, sugar and liqueur until the mixture forms a slowly dissolving ribbon when the beaters are lifted.
Pour the mixture into the top of a double boiler and cook, whisking constantly, over simmering water until very thick, about 3 minutes.
Remover to a large mixing bowl. Whisk in the white chocolate mixture and stir until smooth and cool.
Beat the cream until the peaks are stiff.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: honey sauce for fruit
directions: Combine honey and sour cream.
Just before serving, drizzle over individual fruit cups.
Makes 1 to 1 1/4 cups.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage and pour off grease.
Add onion, garlic, celery and green pepper to sausage; simmer until tender.
Wash rice and add to mixture along with soups.
Bake in oblong 9 x 13-inch dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: grape conserve
directions: Wash the fruit; remove grapes from stems.
Remove skins from pulp.
Cook pulp until soft; strain to remove seeds.
Place the skins and strained pulp into a preserving kettle.
Extract the juice from oranges and lemons; add juices and rind to the grape mixture and cook about 1 hour.
Measure the sugar and grape mixture to equal amounts.
Add nuts and salt.
Continue to cook until thick.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Cool and pour melted wax on top.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Grease and flour 3 layer cake pans.
Pour batter into pans and bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Place everything into a roaster or large crock-pot.
Cover with the V-8 juice and cook 1 1/2 hours at 350° in the oven or 6 hours in the crock-pot.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: In a 3-quart pan, combine potato mix, amounts of water and milk called for on potato package, clam juice, onion and pepper. Cover and cook until potatoes are cooked.
Add clams, milk and butter.
Bring to boil and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot. Season to taste.

title: caramel icing
directions: Put everything except marshmallows in saucepan.
Place over medium heat and stir constantly until it comes to a boil. Continue cooking 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until bubbly.
Drop in 10 marshmallows.
Take off heat and beat
with beater until smooth and ready to spread.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the butterscotch chips on top. You can also sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bruschetta
directions: Chop the tomatoes into 1/4 inch pieces.
Toss with 2 Tbsp. garlic in a bowl.
Add the basil, vinegar, 1/3 c. olive oil, salt and pepper and mix well.
Let stand at room temperature for at least 15 minutes.
Rub bread with the cut side of the garlic halves and brush bread with 1/4 c. olive oil.
Place on grill rack.
Grill for 5 to 8 minutes or until toasted.
Arrange the bread on a serving plate and top with the tomato mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: pork and corn stuffing bake
directions: Combine soup, stuffing, celery, onion and paprika.
In 9-inch greased pie plate, spoon stuffing.
Arrange chops on stuffing, pressing lightly into stuffing.
Combine sugar and mustard. Spread mixture evenly over chops.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until chops are no longer pink.
Garnish with celery leaves if desired.
Serves 4.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Combine water, salt, carrot and beans in a 6-quart pot.
Simmer until beans are tender.

title: foundation cake
directions: *If self-rising flour is used, omit salt and baking powder.

title: chili-cheese pie
directions: In 8 ounce nonstick skillet, heat 1 teaspoon margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
Add onion and garlic; saute about 3 minutes.
Add beef, chilies, tomato paste, chili powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and ground pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for about 5 minutes.
Transfer mixture to a 9-inch pie plate and sprinkle with cheese.

title: sage cornbread
directions: Saute onions in iron skillet in margarine until tender. Combine corn meal, sugar and sage in mixing bowl.
Mix onions into corn meal mixture.

title: rice dressing
directions: Saute a little minced onion and garlic in a little oil, then add drained green beans.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook slowly for about 5 to 10 minutes, then add a small amount of water saved from can and a little grated cheese.

title: california strawberries with cream
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar; chill.
Mix sour cream and almond flavoring.
Put strawberries in parfait glasses or serving dishes. Top with sour cream mixture.
Garnish with mint.
Yields 4 servings.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with a mixture of fresh vegetables.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and Crisco together; take out 1 cup.
Add egg, milk, soda and molasses; pour into 9 x 9 pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup flour mixture on top and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: erica's easy applesauce
directions: Wash apples.
Cut apples in quarters.
Cores may be removed, if desired.
Place in large pot. Add water.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes or until apples are soft. Place a large colander over a bowl and press mashed apples through with a large spoon.
The peels and seeds will remain in the colander.

title: marion's mandarin green salad
directions: Place lettuce in salad bowl and top with Mandarin oranges, pecans and onion rings.
Combine the next seven ingredients and pour over salad just before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, onion and salt until tender.
Drain and mash. Add margarine, soup and most of the crumbs.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs.
Dot with additional butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients. Spread into a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cream and mix together last 3 ingredients. Pour on top of cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool thoroughly for 1 hour before cutting into squares.

title: frozen cabbage salad
directions: Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of salt over cabbage and let stand 1 hour. Squeeze out fluid.
Mix cabbage, celery and green pepper.

title: lazy man's stuffed cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in boiling water; cook until slightly soft. Drain.
Brown ground beef and onions until onions are clear and beef loses its pink.
Drain.
Add tomato soup, tomato sauce and water to meat.
Prepare Minute rice as directed on package.
Add meat and tomato mixture.
In an 11 x 15-inch baking pan, layer cabbage and meat-tomato mixture; repeat once more.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons butter and the oil in a large skillet.
A few at a time, brown the chicken pieces well in the hot fat; remove them to a side dish as they are browned and season with salt and pepper.
Pour out the fat from the skillet; let the pan cool for 5 minutes.

title: fried cheese
directions: Cut 1 ounce Sorrento string cheese in half (or keep whole, optional).
Dredge each piece of string cheese in flour, dip in egg and then coat with bread crumbs.
Place on a plate in a single layer.
Refrigerate uncovered for one
hour.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: In a medium saucepan combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt; cook over medium heat.
Bring mixture to a boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
After boiling for 5 minutes, add chocolate morsels and remove from heat. Stir well until smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Makes 2 1/4 pounds. Enjoy!

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook mixed vegetables according to box.
Drain and cool. Combine with remaining vegetables.
Prepare dressing.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Add butter, eggs and nuts.
Bake in two greased oblong pans, 8 x 12-inch or smaller ones.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Melt in top of double boiler marshmallows and milk.
Pour hot over lime jello and stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and stir to dissolve.
Add crushed pineapple.
Cool.
Blend in whipped cream.

title: cherry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder. Add to creamed butter and sugar; mix well.
To this add the eggs, one at a time, slightly beaten.
To this add candied pineapple first, dates, cherries and pecans.
Bake in moderate oven at 250° for 2 or 2 1/2 hours.
Let cool in pan overnight.
Cook in square pan lined with wax paper.
Spray with Pam.
Cook this several days before using.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Slice wieners approximately 1/2-inch thick.
In skillet, mix all ingredients.
Cover and simmer slowly 10 minutes.

title: mock clotted cream(dried milk method)
directions: Beat margarine and sugar together.
By degrees, add dried milk.
Flavour with vanilla and beat until very smooth.
(GE)

title: seven layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce and fill bowl half way full.
Mix together celery and onions.
Sprinkle over lettuce.
Add peas.
Spread mayonnaise 1/4-inch deep.
Sprinkle cheese and top with bacon bits.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and light corn syrup in a 3 qt. saucepan over medium heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 13 x 9 inch pan.
Let harden.
Melt over hot water (double boiler) semi-sweet chocolate morsels and
butterscotch morsels.
Stir to blend. Spread over Krispies mixture.
Chill until firm in refrigerator. Cut into bars.
Yield: 48 2 x 1 inch bars.

title: savory ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients and saute.
Pour over ribs and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring to a boil, stirring.

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix meal and flour.
Add onions and squash.
Stir in eggs and milk to make stiff batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.

title: banana walnut muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, walnuts, soda and salt together.
Combine bananas, butter, egg and milk and vanilla in separate bowl.
Add banana mixture to dry ingredients, mixing until just combined. Bake until toothpick comes out clean, about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: old time sweet tater puddin
directions: Mash butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs.
Add sweet potatoes, spices and milk.
Pour in greased pan and sprinkle top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Crumble beef into a 4 to 5 quart Dutch oven.
Add onion and cook over medium-high heat for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring often until beef is lightly browned.
Quarter and core cabbage.
Cut crosswise in one-inch wide strips.
You should have about 8 cups.
Add to meat mixture.
Cover and cook over medium heat 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally until cabbage wilts.
Stir in tomatoes, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Serves 4.

title: mexican coffee
directions: Place coffee and cinnamon in filter basket of coffee maker. Add water and brew. In a saucepan, blend milk, chocolate syrup and sugar, stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Combine milk mixture and brewed coffee. Stir in vanilla. Pour into cups to serve. Top each serving with whipped cream with ground cinnamon sprinkled on top.

title: cocoa pebbles s'mores bars
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with foil.
Grease bottom and sides of foil-lined pan.
Place graham crackers on bottom of pan, cutting crackers to fit.
Microwave chocolate and 2 tablespoons butter in microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes.
Stir until melted.
Spread 1/2 of the melted chocolate over graham crackers.
Microwave remaining 4 tablespoons butter in 4 quart microwavable bowl on High 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows.
Mix to coat. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes or until melted, stirring after 45 seconds. Add cereal.
Mix to coat well.
Press firmly over chocolate-coated graham crackers in pan.
Drizzle with remaining melted chocolate. Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook meat and onions; drain. Add taco seasoning according to package. Add corn, beans, tomatoes and water.
Simmer 10 minutes. Serve with grated cheese and chips.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on large cookie sheet.
Bake until done (watch carefully).
Cool.

title: second time around cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Add 1/4 cup water and donuts.
Stir well and pour into 12 x 18-inch shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Bake unpicked pastry with 2 layers of foil for 5 minutes at 450°.
Remove foil; bake 5 to 7 minutes more (keep warm).
Cook sausage, onions and garlic until meat is done.
Drain.
Stir in chili peppers.
In another saucepan, combine cheese and flour; add cream.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted.
Add hot sauce. Blend hot cream mixture into beaten eggs slowly.
Add meat mixture.
Pour into pastry.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Let stand.
Serve with picante sauce, sour cream and guacamole.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients; store in an airtight container.
To make 1 cup, place a heaping teaspoonful in cup and fill with hot water.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans and pie crust.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: ice cream surprise
directions: In a 9 X 13 pan place as many of the ice cream sandwiches to line bottom of pan. Squeeze all of the caramel magic shell sauce onto ice cream sandwiches. Crumble 1 Butterfinger candy bar on top. Top with cool whip then sprinkle 2nd butterfinger candy bar crushed on top of dessert. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: pears with spicy lime, chile and peanut chutney
directions: Cut each pear lengthwise into quarters.
Using a melon baller, create a well in the center of each quarter.
In a small bowl, prepare chutney by mixing together the next seven ingredients. Spoon chutney into hollowed out section of pear quarters.
Add a sprig of mint for garnish.
Place on serving tray.

title: jello cream salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boiling point.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate until it begins to set.
Stir in cream cheese.
Fold in whipping cream and nuts.
Add cherries, if desired.
Mold.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Put over heat and add vinegar, onion, salt and paprika.
Chill until about to set.
Beat the gelatin mixture into the stiffly whipped cream.
Fold in the cucumbers.
Rinse individual molds, fill them with mousse.
When they are thoroughly chilled, invert them onto a garnished plate. Serves 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns with sour cream and margarine. Add 1 cup of the grated cheese, onion, salt and pepper. Slowly mix in the can of soup. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix remaining 1 cup cheese with corn flake crumbs. Sprinkle on top of potato mixture in dish. Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, syrup and butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter melts and mixture is steaming. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 325° until set.

title: broccoli-rice casserole *
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add all three soups, undiluted to make a sauce.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in casserole dish.
Place drained broccoli on top and sprinkle with paprika and grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable rice bake
directions: Mix first
ingredients
in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Put cheese on top and dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, beat 1 1/2 cups sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; mix well.
In small bowl, combine the 2 tablespoons each of sugar and cinnamon.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until set immediately.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: super rotel dip
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage until brown and crumbly.
Add Ro-Tel and cheese and melt on low heat.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Heat margarine until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole or 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until bubbly, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Combine ground chuck, onion, soy sauce, mushrooms, pepper and mix lightly.
Shape into patties 1 1/2-inch thick.
Wrap each patty with one slice bacon.
Secure with pick.
Grill 3 to 6 minutes or to desired doneness.

title: pink divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in saucepan. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Cover and bring to a boil.
Cook for a minute or two to wash down sugar crystals.
Remove cover. Cook, without stirring, until syrup reaches hard ball stage, 260°, or until syrup is slightly brittle when dropped in cold water. Beat egg whites until frothy.
Continue beating, adding Jell-O slowly. Beat until candy is creamy. Stir in nuts. Candy sets quickly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix together cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt; beat well.
Stir in chocolate tidbits; set aside.
Sift flour, 1/2 cup sugar, cocoa, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt into mixing bowl.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; beat well. Fill baking cups 1/3 full of chocolate batter.
Top each with a heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 5-hour stew
directions: Toss everything into a roaster pan and let cook at 275° for 5 hours.
Can also use slow-cooker for 7 to 8 hours.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: boston butt pork roast
directions: Preheat oven and roasting pan to 350°. Salt and pepper 1 side of the roast. Place seasoned side of roast down on preheated pan. Bake for 20 minutes. Season top side of roast. Turn roast over and decrease oven heat to 325°. Roast for about 2 1/2 hours at 325° (longer time will be needed if larger roast). Turn roast over and add vegetables around base of roast in pan, with potatoes on bottom, covered by the carrots and at least 2 pieces of the apples on top of the roast. Cover the roasting pan after adding the vegetables. Add hot water to depth of about 1-inch. Bake for an additional hour or hour and 15 minutes or until vegetables are done and meat shreds easily. Remember to check water level occasionally. You don't want it to go dry.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed, omitting 1 cup of the milk and adding sour cream and Cool Whip.
In large bowl, layer with vanilla wafers, the sliced bananas and pudding.
Layer until all is used, ending with pudding on top.
Add Cool Whip on top and keep chilled until ready to use.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 inch pan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup, level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and lemon peel.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in margarine until mixture is the consistency of coarse meal.
Add milk, eggs, and vanilla; stir until well blended.
Pour 3/4 of batter into prepared pan.
Top with blueberries.
Spoon remaining batter over blueberries.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Break chocolate into heavy (large) mixing bowl.
Add whipped marshmallow, chopped walnuts and vanilla.
In a large pan, heat to melt butter and margarine.
Then bring to a rolling boil once boiling starts.
Let boil for exactly 6 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add to mixture in bowl.
Mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill overnight and enjoy.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Roll biscuits in butter, then roll in brown sugar.
Sprinkle on cinnamon.

title: london broil
directions: Blend all ingredients in shallow pan.
Marinate steak, turning occasionally, several hours or overnight.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes on each side.
Slice on diagonal.

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, oleo, eggs and flour to make stiff dough.
Grease top; cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Form into balls and cover. Let rise until double in size again, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or 12 cup Bundt pan.
Beat butter and cream cheese together in mixing bowl until well blended.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Blend in vanilla. Sift flour and salt together and blend into cream mixture.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: glazed fruit and franks
directions: In saucepan, combine preserves, lemon juice, cornstarch and cinnamon. Cook and stir until well blended and slightly thickened. Stir in franks and pineapple. Heat through. Just before serving, stir in apples and oranges. Serve warm.

title: chicken breast with honey chutney and pears
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pears and lemon juice. Melt margarine in skillet.
Add chicken; saute. Transfer to shallow glass baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Place pears and lemon juice combination on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until done.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place nuts in the bottom of Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each piece in sugar and cinnamon, mixed together. Put in greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter; add brown sugar, water and remaining cinnamon and sugar.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on plate; serve warm.

title: hot cheese yummies
directions: Add mayonnaise to grated cheese.
Add chopped ripe olives and green onions.
Mix and spread on English muffins.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cut into fourths to serve.
Freezes well.

title: chinese pickled beets
directions: Mix everything in saucepan and cook until mixture thickens. Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper in a bag.
Shake 3 or 4 pieces of chicken in bag to coat.
Melt butter in large skillet; add chicken to brown.
Add onions, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes longer.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, garlic, red pepper and oregano.
Cook, covered, until tender, about 30 minutes.
Add sherry wine; mix well and bring to boiling point.
Serve with spaghetti.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mushroom appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese, bacon and mushroom caps. Broil about 10 minutes or until clear liquid seeps from mushrooms.
Serve hot.

title: squash dressing
directions: Melt oleo; saute onion and celery.
Add undiluted soup, squash, cornbread soaked in milk and sage.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Stir-fry onion in bacon drippings for 2 minutes.
Add rice and stir-fry for 7 to 8 minutes.
Add soy sauce, water and crumbled bacon.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Pur eggs on top of rice mixture.
Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until eggs are cooked.

title: banana bread 2
directions: Beat flour, baking soda, salt, sugar, margarine and eggs 2 1/2 minutes on high.
Add sour cream and beat on low.
Add bananas and vanilla and beat on low.
Optional:
Add walnuts and beat on low. Add raisins; cover raisins with sugar and drop in batter that has been poured into loaf pan.
Push raisins into batter individually with knife.
Butter and flour bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed, drain.
Rinse with cold water, drain. Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice, salt and sugar.
Combine with macaroni, celery seed, tomato, celery, pimiento and green pepper.
Serve on salad greens, garnish with radish roses. Serves 6.

title: sauerbraten steaks
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups water, vinegar, sugar, salt, cloves, peppercorns and
bay leaves in saucepan;
bring to boil.
Pour over sliced
onions;
cool.
Stir
in oil.
Pour marinade over steak; refrigerate
to
hours,
turning
at least once. Remove steaks from marinade to absorbent paper; pat dry.
Heat drippings to 350°.

title: meat in mushroom sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in covered 2-quart dish and bake at 300° for four hours.
Delicious!

title: mama crow's raisin nut jam cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs well, then add jam.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients and beat well after each addition.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake 40 minutes at 300° (or until toothpick inserted in center of layer comes out clean).
Cool completely on racks.

title: bar-b-que'd pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a large skillet and cover with water. Brown the chops.
Remove from skillet and brown the onions.
Put chops back in the skillet with the onions and add vinegar, brown sugar, and ketchup.
Add water to cover.
Cook over high heat until it starts to boil.
Reduce heat to low, let simmer until gravy thickens, about 2 hours.

title: shrimp bake
directions: Mix well and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with 3/4 cup grated Swiss cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mama fisackerly tea cakes
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Mix well.
Add flour slowly.
Form into balls on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown on edge (15 to 20 minutes).

title: peanut butter chocolate cups
directions: In microwave, melt chocolate, butter and shortening. Stir until smooth. Place in miniature foil baking cups in miniature muffin pan. Put 1 teaspoon chocolate mixture in each cup. Microwave peanut butter until melted. Spoon into cups and cover with chocolate mixture. Refrigerate. Makes 1 dozen.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a 13 x 9-inch or 2 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Corn flakes can be crushed and mixed with melted butter for a topping, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with lemon twist and parsley, if desired.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion, broccoli and celery. Cook over low heat a few minutes, then add soup, cheese and rice.
Pour in baking dish and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
(This may be cooked in microwave.)

title: marbled double chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 8 or 9-inch square baking pan with foil, extending edges over sides of pan.
In a small mixing bowl, beat butter, 1/2 cup sugar and salt until smooth.
Stir together flour and cocoa; gradually add to butter mixture, beating until soft dough is formed.
Press dough onto bottom of prepared pan. Beat cream cheese and remaining 1/2 cup sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.

title: robert redford cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan according to package directions.
While cake is still warm, poke holes (about a dozen) across top of cake with the end of a wooden spoon.
Let cool slightly.
Pour sweetened condensed milk and topping into holes and over cake.
Let stand a few minutes, then spread with Cool Whip. Sprinkle crushed candy bars over top.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: pumpkin cheese bread
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add combined dry ingredients, mixing until just moistened.
Fold in nuts.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
You can use either a 13 x 9-inch rectangle pan or a Bundt pan.

title: chocolate bottom bites
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; add to dry ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon batter into paper-lined miniature muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.

title: cream cheese cherry pie
directions: To cherries, add 1 cup sugar and the flour.
Cook in saucepan until thick; refrigerate to cool.
Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add the vanilla and a little cream to make it smooth.
Whip the cream and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Fill the cooled pie crust with cheese filling.
Pour cherry mixture on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread as directed on package. Crumble and let cool. Chop pepper, tomato and onions. Add to cornbread, then add about 3 cups of Miracle Whip. Chill.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off grease.
Add taco seasoning.
Spoon half of hamburger into 2-quart casserole, then beans, then cheese, then chips.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy white chili
directions: In a large saucepan, saut chicken, onion, peppers and garlic powder in oil until chicken is no longer pink. Add beans, broth and seasonings. Bring to a boil, then simmer uncovered for 30 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Sift twice with soda.
Set aside. Cream butter and add sugar slowly, beating constantly to cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Stir in sour cream. Add flour mixture, one-half cup at a time.
Beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
turn into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple side dish
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Combine pineapple, sugar, bread and eggs.
Pour into baking dish over melted butter.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Form into logs. about 2 inches long and about 1/2 inch in diameter.
Put them into freezer till frozen.
Oh about an hour or so.
Melt 1 package of chocolate chips. 1/2 bar of wax.
Dip logs into chips and wax.
Put logs onto wax paper.
Its a lot easier to store.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box; set aside. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Sprinkle coconut on top of nuts.
Pour cake mixture over coconut.

title: crust (never fail)
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large pan until it is crumbly. Place 1 egg, 1 teaspoon of vinegar in 1 cup and mix.
Fill remainder of cup with milk to make 1 cup.
Mix with flour until it will come off of your hands.

title: ragu no-boiling lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In bowl,

combine Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and eggs. In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread 1/2 of one jar of pasta sauce. Layer 4 uncooked noodles, then 1/2 jar of pasta sauce and 1/2 of the Ricotta cheese mixture; repeat. Top with remaining 4 uncooked noodles and rest of pasta sauce. Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake 1 hour. Remove foil and sprinkle remaining cheeses. Bake, uncovered, an additional 10 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: fruited green salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine salad greens and fruit; toss.
Add dressing and poppy seed; toss to coat.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar and let stand for 30 minutes.
Beat egg.
Add oil and vanilla and add to apple mixture.
Mix all other ingredients together and add to apple mixture.
Grease and flour an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes to 45 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: beef and biscuits casserole
directions: Brown meat in onion; stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic powder.
Simmer.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with biscuits, combine half of the cheese, sour cream and egg; then mix with meat.
Spoon the meat mixture over the biscuits.
Sprinkle the rest of cheese on top of the meat mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: swiss vegetable medley (microwave)
directions: Combine veggies, soup, 1/2 c. cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can Durkee fried onions.
Pour into the 1 qt. casserole dish. Microwave on high 10-12 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove and sprinkle remaining onions over top.
Microwave until cheese is melted.

title: sesame chicken nuggets
directions: Wash chicken and cut into cubes (approximately 1 to 2-inch in size).
Set aside to drain on paper towels.
Mix beaten egg, milk, salt and sesame seed in medium size bowl.
Add chicken to egg mixture.
Coat each piece of chicken with flour.
After all chicken is coated with flour, heat shortening on medium until ready to fry.
Add nuggets a few at a time to keep them from sticking together, turning them 2 or 3 times until they are tender and golden brown.
Serve with sauces such as barbecue, honey mustard or sweet-n-sour.

title: taco dip
directions: In a bowl, blend together cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix.
Spread over dinner plate.
Layer the remaining ingredients on top.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy chicken hawaiian
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot or casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and pur over.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or in crock-pot all day.
Serve with rice.

title: homemade dumplings
directions: Mix flour, celery salt, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix in butter until even particles are formed.
Add milk and blend.
Cook until tender in chicken broth.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
In top of double boiler, beat egg yolks; add 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and salt. Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add softened gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat, add lemon rind and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff. Fold in cooled lemon mixture and then pour into the pie shell. Refrigerate until set.
Spread with whipped cream just before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together thoroughly. Add eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Add vanilla. Bake in a well-greased and floured tube cake pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Combine the scallions, fresh tomatoes and peppers in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in the pureed tomatoes, water and lime juice. Stir in the oil and parsley; season with salt and pepper. Refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve.
Serve with your favorite corn tortilla chips.
A great summer dip!
Yields 8 cups.

title: wild strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, jello and cornstarch. Cook at a slow rolling boil for 5 minutes. Put berries in baked pie shells. Pour mixture over berries. Refrigerate. Top with whipped cream or sour cream when served. Makes 2 pies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well.
Salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir when half done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 11 x 13-inch greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: corned beef and noodles
directions: Alternate in layers in greased baking dish.
Top with 3/4 cup crumbs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix all together well; put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat 2-inches deep of oil in skillet.
Heat oil until hot, but not smoking.
Take batter, pour it through funnel into hot oil, moving in a circular motion, then crisscross until you've made a cake the size of a plate or smaller.
When lightly browned, remove and drain on paper towels.
Dredge or sprinkle in powdered sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon powder.
Best when eaten warm.

title: chicken mini-drumsticks
directions: Remove tips from chicken wings.
Combine pineapple juice, beer, soy sauce, brown sugar, onion, ginger and garlic.
Stir together until sugar is dissolved.
Add chicken, stirring to coat well.
Cover and marinate at room temperature for about 1 hour. Drain chicken; reserve marinade.
Melt margarine in a large frying pan over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook, browning on all sides.
add 1/2 cup reserved marinade to chicken.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, over low heat for about 15 minutes or until fork can be inserted into chicken with ease.
Keep chicken moist by using additional marinade as needed.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to butter mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Bake in a well-greased lightly floured tube pan (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until straw inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing.
This can be baked and stored for a couple of days.
Keep cool.

title: pineapple parfait salad
directions: Dissolve jello and water.
Add pineapple.
Chill
until slightly thickened.
Soften and blend cream cheese and sour cream. Stir in jello mixture.
Add nuts and chill.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: In large pan, heat chili.
Cut cheese into small squares and add to chili.
When cheese is melted, add sour cream and sauteed onion.
Mix well and serve hot with chips.

title: bill salveson's mozzarella marinara
directions: Cut Mozzarella cheese into slices approximately 1/2-inch thick.

title: crusty coated eggplant
directions: Cut stems off eggplant and slice 1/2 to 5/8-inch thickness. In a bowl, beat in egg.
In second bowl, mix cracker crumbs, seasonings and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Spread butter in a 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Dip each slice of eggplant in egg.
Drain briefly, then coat with cracker crumbs.
Arrange slices in single layer in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes, turning once, in a 425° oven.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop onto cookie sheet or put in pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cracker pie
directions: Whip the cream and add sugar and preserves.
Put mixture into pie crust; sprinkle top with coconut and refrigerate.

title: best ever cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well; save 1/4 for the top.
Put the remainder into the bottom of a glass baking dish (8 1/2 x 11-inch).
Grease the baking dish first.

title: sausage cheese casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage; drain.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard and mix.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and sausage and mix.
Put in 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let it set for 15 minutes before slicing.

title: sausage-beef casserole
directions: Brown sausages and beef chuck cubes in electric skillet.
Add onion, garlic, green peppers, potatoes, kidney beans, basil, salt and pepper.
Add bouillon and cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check from time to time.
Add more bouillon if needed. Juices may be thickened for gravy.

title: lipton onion burger
directions: In large bowl combine beaten egg, Lipton onion soup mix, water, bread crumbs and ground meat.
Shape into patties.
Grill or broil until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream the butter; gradually add the sugar and beat 10 to 15 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Strain green beans and artichoke hearts.
Cut or mash green beans into small pieces.
Cut artichoke into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together, and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with additional bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cut dates in quarters and pour boiling water over them.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
When cool, add beaten egg, flour sifted with soda and cream of tartar, nuts and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Watch oven; do not get too hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, eggs and milk.
Add crushed rusks and mix well. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix all together and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix well pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes; cool completely.
Cream the cheese and blend in 1 cup sugar.
Add Cool Whip; mix well. Spread over cooled pretzels.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add frozen strawberries, slightly thickened.
Pour over Cool Whip layer.
Chill until firm.

title: pizza dipping sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in small saucepan; cook over medium heat until hot.
Serve with warm bread sticks and chips.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat together the eggs and milk.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix both mixtures together and beat with a whip until smooth.
Pour in hot oil.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Wash peas and place in large pan with cold water.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let sit for 1 hour.
Fry bacon slowly until brown, drain.
Add Tabasco sauce, bacon and salt to peas.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer, stirring frequently for 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Should be moist, but not wet.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition is made.
Add bananas.
Next add dry ingredients and nuts (walnuts or pecans).
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: parmesan potato sticks
directions: Scrub and peel potatoes; cut lengthwise into quarters.
Cut each quarter into 3 strips.
Roll in melted butter; then roll in combined remaining ingredients.
Place potato sticks in a single layer on a cookie sheet.
Drizzle melted butter over potatoes. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Yield:
6 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: After popping corn, sift through to remove unpopped kernels. Melt caramels, water and butter together over medium-low heat, stirring constantly so it doesn't burn. When melted, pour over corn. Stir so it is well coated. Shape into balls and store in airtight containers.

title: little reubens
directions: Cook the drained sauerkraut for 5 minutes with the diced onions and 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix corned beef with relish and mustard.
Spread on slice of party bread.
Top with heaping tablespoonful of sauerkraut mixture and slice of Swiss cheese. Broil until cheese melts.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: chocolate pudding stacks
directions: In microwave, sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup cold water.
Let stand 1 minute to soften.
Microwave on high 20 seconds, stir; rotate cup 1/4 turn;
microwave high 20 seconds.
Prepare pudding with skim milk following package directions.
Add unflavored gelatin and vanilla to pudding, stir until blended.
Place 8 graham crackers in bottom of 11 X 7 inch dish.
Spread with 1/2 the pudding.
Place 1/2 the banana slices on pudding.
Repeat layers ending with bananas.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
To serve cut into 8 squares.
Top with 1 tub whipped topping.

title: coconut balls
directions: Roll in balls, then dip in chocolate with 1/2 block to pack.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites and vanilla to soft peaks; gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Mix crumbs, nuts and baking powder; fold into beaten egg whites.
Spread evenly in greased and floured 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool completely.
Whip the cream or use Cool Whip.
Cut pie. Serve topped with cream.
Serves 6.

title: pizza sauce to can
directions: Wash and core tomatoes.
Cut them up and put them through a juicer (should be about 6 quarts of juice).
Put juice in a large heavy kettle and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick and volume is reduced to about 1/2 the original measure.
Ladle into hot pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover with lids and bands and process in a boiling water bath canner for 35 minutes. Makes 6 pints.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: In a 10 x 13-inch pan, layer chopped lettuce, onion, celery, peas and chestnuts.
Spread on mayonnaise, covering all ingredients.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar over top of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses over mayonnaise (Parmesan first).
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap or pan lid and refrigerate 24 hours.
When ready to serve, top with bacon and tomatoes.
Serves twelve.

title: shrimp and scallop casserole
directions: Marinate seafood in soy sauce 15 minutes. While seafood is marinating, melt butter in saucepan. Add parsley and crushed garlic. Remove seafood from sauce.
Place in a shallow casserole or baking dish. Top with mushrooms, water chestnuts and bean sprouts.
Pour butter mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
(Test shrimp for doneness.)

title: picture perfect petal cake
directions: In a small bowl, toss coconut and food coloring until evenly coated; set aside. Place angel food cake on a large serving platter. Frost top and sides with whipped topping; sprinkle on coconut. Cut cake into 8 or 10 slices, then very carefully pull out each slice just a bit to resemble flower petals. Spoon strawberry halves in center. Any leftovers should be refrigerated.

title: corn lovers special
directions: In 13 X 9 baking dish place both cans of corn.
Mix 2 eggs with corn bread mix. Set aside.
Saute onions.
Layer on top of corn.
Place corn bread mixture on top.
Drizzle melted butter over top and bake for 40 minutes at 400.

title: baked onion rings
directions: Mix egg substitute, salt and pepper.
Dip onion rings into egg mixture and coat with bread crumbs.
Place in single layer on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until all is mixed well.
Butter 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and pour in.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry bundt cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour half into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Put about 1/2 can of cherry pie filling into center of cake.
Do not touch sides of pan with cherry filling. Pour the rest of cake mix over the top.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: zucchini and cream cheese
directions: Cut unpeeled zucchini into thin slices and boil until tender but still crunchy.
Drain thoroughly.
Melt cheese and butter and mix with garlic powder and zucchini.
Put in a baking dish and crumble crackers on top.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: taco ring
