directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Brown beef, drain and add taco seasoning mix along with the water, and cheese. Place crescent rolls in a ring around a large round stone with the pointed end facing right overlapping each other then place meat mixture in the center of the crescent rolls. Take the end of each crescent roll and wrap around the other end until circle so complete. Bake in the oven until the rolls become golden brown, about 10 minutes. Use the rest of the ingredients to garnish with.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar; add 3/4 cup shortening, brown sugar and buttermilk.
Add bananas, eggs and vanilla; beat for 1 minute.
Fold in 3/4 cup chopped pecans dusted with flour.
Bake in a tube pan.
Make a thick paste of confectioners sugar and enough sour cream to dribble over cake for frosting.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Bake chicken breasts topped with margarine at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, turning every 15 minutes.
Pour off margarine and chicken fat.
Cover chicken with half the barbecue sauce and bake 30 minutes.
Turn and cover other side and bake 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in three layers. Place 1 in bottom of bowl.
Mix pudding mix and place 1/3 on cake layer.
Top with blueberry filling.
Mix pecans with Cool Whip.
Put 1/3 on top.
Place second layer cake.
Add drained pineapple, 1/3 of pudding mix and 1/3 of Cool Whip.
Put third layer with rest of pudding mix, strawberry mix and Cool Whip.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix cranberries, apples and sugar.
Melt margarine.
Add Rice Krispies, brown sugar and flour.
Fold into cranberry mixture. Sprinkle with nuts over the top.
Bake in a large buttered casserole (9 x 13-inch), uncovered, for 45 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: gourmets delight pecan cheese dip
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook over boiling water until thick.
Cool slightly.
Beat in cheese.
Grate in green pepper and onion.
Add pecans.
Let season 2 hours.
Good for potato chips or Fritos.

title: italian-style potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix potatoes, sauce mix and water in ungreased 2-quart round casserole; stir in milk.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden brown and potatoes are tender.

title: kourabiedes(crescent cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Measure butter, shortening, 2 cups sugar, egg, liqueur, almond extract and 2 cups flour into a large mixer bowl. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly. Beat 1 minute on medium speed, scraping the bowl occasionally. Stir in remaining flour.
Knead until smooth. Shape 1-inch pieces of dough into crescent shapes.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until cookies are light brown on bottoms, 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar on cookies while hot.
Cool on wire racks. Flavor mellows after 2 or 3 days. Store cookies in airtight containers at room temperature no longer than 9 days or in freezer no longer than 2 months.
Makes about 11 dozen.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat eggs, one at a time, into mixture.
Add additional ingredients.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onions, cheese, sunflower seeds and bacon. Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Stir in broccoli mix.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all with electric mixer well.
Chill and enjoy.

title: okra gumbo
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and pepper in oil until tender. Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat 15 minutes. Stir frequently.
Serve immediately.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lime and pineapple holiday salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Heat this and add jello.
Dissolve.
While still hot, add marshmallows; cool.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Whip cream and fold other ingredients into this.
Chill until firm.

title: baked ham
directions: Cut rind off ham.
Combine dry ingredients and add enough juice to make a dough that can be rolled over fat.
Cover part of ham with dough.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes per pound, 4 or 5 hours for a 15 pound ham, basting every 30 minutes.
Take dough off and finish with brown sugar or any favorite way of browning ham.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water until just tender.
Drain.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in mayonnaise, onions, green pepper, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add zucchini; toss.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or 5 minutes in microwave.

title: pistachio cake
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, orange juice, oil and pudding mix. Blend at low speed of electric mixer 1 minute, then high speed 3 minutes. Pour 2/3 of batter in nonstick (Pam sprayed) pan or greased and floured Bundt pan. To remaining 1/3 of batter, add chocolate and blend.
Pour over top of batter in pan. Marbelize with knife. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done. Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out onto plate to cool completely. Glaze if desired.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Butter pie plate (10-inch Pyrex).

title: non-edible christmas tree ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients; knead and shape ornaments by using cookie cutters or other kitchen tools to cut them out.
Push in metal buttons or other decorations that won't melt.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Make color with food color or decorate after baking with colored glue, glitter glue, etc.
Easy and fun!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Melt butter in skillet, add onion and broccoli.
Simmer until onion is transparent and broccoli is tender.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Mix well and remove from heat.
Add rice.
Bake in buttered pan, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Put all in blender and mix. Put corn in last.
Blend it very little.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: carrot crunch cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, oil and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, water and vanilla.
Sift together all-purpose flour, baking soda, nutmeg and salt.
Add to bowl, along with whole-wheat flour.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Make large drop cookies, well spaced, on greased baking sheet, using about 1/3 cup batter for each. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: chicken and mushroom casserole
directions: Melt butter in heavy covered skillet.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Remove chicken and drain excess fat.
Stir in soup and loose pan drippings.
Add sour cream, stirring until well mixed. Add chicken.
Cover and simmer over very low heat until tender, about 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms last couple of minutes. Serve over pasta or rice.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter. Let cool a little. Add marshmallows and nuts. Mix well. Put coconut on wax paper and put mixture onto coconut. Shape into roll. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for 48 hours. Slice and serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with chopped onion; drain grease.
Tear tortillas and place in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Heat soup and tomatoes. Layer tortillas, meat, beans and soup mixture.
Continue layering until all is used up.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: lemonade punch
directions: Prepare lemonade concentrate with water according to the directions on the can.
Add chilled cranberry juice cocktail and ginger ale.
Add ice and mix well.
Float scoops of sherbet on top.
Serve as is or over ice cubes, if desired.
Yields 25 (6 ounce) cups.

title: fruit cocktail squares
directions: Cream sugar and eggs together. Sift and add flour, soda and salt. Add fruit cocktail and vanilla. Use 15 X 10 X 1 inch pan. Grease and flour cookie sheet. Pour batter in cookie sheet, sprinkle with coconut and nuts (optional). Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until golden brown. While cookie dough is still warm, drizzle with the following glaze over dough.

title: cherry pineapple cake
directions: Beat until smooth.
Pour into 3 cake pans.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: 20-minute chicken parmesan
directions: Using palm of hand, flatten chicken to even thickness.
Dip chicken into egg, then into crumbs to coat.
In skillet, over medium heat, in hot margarine, brown chicken on both sides.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes. Sprinkle with cheeses and parsley.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken spitsade
directions: Fry chicken (which has been skinned), coated with salt, pepper, garlic powder and paprika.
Put fried chicken in large pan with 1/2 cup of frying oil.
Add olives, mushrooms and peppers to chicken.
Add 1/2 cup wine for flavor.
Cook for at least 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with rice.

title: sun-dried tomato dip
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving 1 tablespoon oil.
In food processor, place oil, tomatoes, cheese and garlic.
Process until well blended, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Serve with pita chips or bagel chips.
Also good with raw vegetables.

title: hash brown potato pie
directions: Beat together eggs and milk. Stir in hash browns, onion, salt and hot pepper sauce. Stir in 1 cup of the cheese and half of the bacon. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until center is set. Sprinkle remaining cheese and bacon over the top. Continue to bake 3 to 4 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Beat eggs slightly in mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients. Cover bottom of a 6-inch skillet with peanut oil and heat skillet. Pour 1/4 of the mixture in this and cook over low heat until brown on one side.
Turn carefully and cook until brown on other side.
Serve with Brown Sauce.

title: salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Combine filling and oranges and pineapple.
Add sliced bananas just before serving.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half length-wise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4 inch shell.
Combine onion, mushrooms, celery, margarine, and tomato in a microwavable dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook 4 - 6 minutes.
Drain.
Add crackers, egg, grated cheese, parmesan cheese, salt, and pepper.
Mound this stuffing in each zucchini shell. Cover and microwave 5 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In large saucepan, melt peanut butter, 1 cup of sweetened condensed milk and 2 tablespoons butter; stir occasionally. Remove from heat; stir in peanuts.
Spread mixture into wax paper-lined 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: roast goose
directions: If necessary, singe and clean the goose.
Pat dry.
Rub the cavity with salt.
Combine the other ingredients and stuff into the goose.
Secure the opening with skewers and truss.
Prick the skin thoroughly with a fork so that fat will run out.
Put goose on rack in a roasting pan, breast side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roast in 350° oven for 3 1/2 hours.
At the end of one hour, add a cup of water to the pan and baste every half hour with the drippings.
Serves 8.

title: baked beans(impressive and easy)
directions: Season the ground beef according to your family preference. I use black pepper, seasoning salt, garlic powder, and onion powder. Put all ingredients into a skillet, stir and heat.

title: pam's sweet trash(low-fat)
directions: Combine popcorn, pretzels and cereals in a large pan or Dutch oven that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Combine sugar, Butter Buds, syrup
and lite salt in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Quickly stir in baking soda.
Pour over popcorn mixture and stir together quickly.
Mix until well coated. Spread on 4 cookie sheets that have been lined with foil and sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool until hardened.
When cool and hardened, break apart and store in an airtight container.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion (and sausage if used).
Cook until done.
Add tomatoes, salt, chili powder, corn and olives.
Cook until heated.
Place into an 11 x 7-inch oblong pan.
Mix cornmeal, milk and eggs; spread on top.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cheese browns.

title: creamy tarragon dip
directions: In a blender or food processor with knife blade attached, blend the first 8 ingredients until smooth.
Pour mixture into small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: slow oven beef stew
directions: Combine meat, onions, celery, carrots, tomato juice, tapioca, sugar, salt, pepper and basil in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook in a slow oven (300°) for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir potatoes and green beans (undrained) into stew and continue cooking, covered, for 1 hour or until meat and vegetables are done.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan.
Add marshmallows and cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated.
Press warm mixture evenly and firmly into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yield: 24 squares when cool (2 x 2-inches).

title: classic chocolate cake
directions: Stir together cocoa and boiling water in small bowl until smooth; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Blend in eggs.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Blend in reserved cocoa mixture.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese and gently fold in pineapple.
Add Cool Whip, then add nuts.
Fold in strawberries.
Freeze.
Serves 10.

title: malakoff(cool, summer dessert)
directions: Mix 2 whole eggs with milk, sugar and cornstarch.
Mix cold and cook until thick (like a pudding).
Stir constantly to avoid lumps.
Cool.

title: pattie's chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff. Add sugar, vanilla and nuts. Pour into an 8-inch greased pie pan. Mold sides up to form a pie shell. Bake at 300° for 35 minutes. Melt chocolate in water and cool. Beat whipping cream until thick. Mix vanilla into cooled chocolate and fold together with whipped cream. Pour into cooled meringue pie shell. Chill.

title: potato 'n cheese bake
directions: Melt cheeses and oleo.
Add half and half.
Add salt; put frozen potatoes in a large casserole.
Pour cheese mixture over the potatoes.
Let set 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; boil until soft.
Mash with butter and sour cream.
Add green onions and salt; blend until potatoes are fluffy.
Put into a casserole dish; sprinkle with more of the salt to taste, if desired.
Add slices of Velveeta cheese to cover top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and cheese and put in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle combined crackers and cheese on top. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick oleo in casserole dish.
Mix well all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: date loaf
directions: Beat eggs with a fork.
Add vanilla, sugar and flour, beating with a fork.
Add the date mixture, mixing just to blend.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut butter crunchies(diabetic)
directions: Thoroughly blend peanut butter and honey.
Stir in 1/2 c. Corn Flake crumbs.
Form into 24 small balls and roll in remaining Corn Flake crumbs.
Chill.

title: apple brownie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and dry ingredients.
Mix.
Mixture will be dry.
Add apples and nuts.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine smoked ham, fresh pork, eggs and bread or cracker crumbs and form into loaf.
Place in roasting pan.
Make sauce of remaining ingredients and pour over loaf.
Bake in 350° oven about an hour, or until done.

title: upper peninsula pastie
directions: Place all ingredients on crust then fold and seal.
Dot with butter and make three slits in crust to allow the steam to escape. Bake in center rack at 400° for 1 hour.
Serve with brown gravy or catsup.

title: watermelon punch
directions: In a blender, puree the watermelon pieces and strain the puree through a very fine sieve set over a pitcher, discarding the solids.
(There should be about 2 1/2 cups juice.)
Stir in the vodka, the Triple Sec and the lime juice; pour the cooler into long-stemmed glasses filled with ice and garnish each drink with a watermelon slice.
Makes 4 to 6 drinks.

title: tortilla roll-ups(makes approximately 6 dozen)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tortillas.
Spread tortillas with mixture, almost to end, and roll up.
Slice into 2-inch lengths.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut the broccoli into small bite-sized pieces.
Cut cauliflower into bite-sized pieces.
Add onion and cheese.
Add dressing (*), then bacon bits last, and toss.

title: lentil casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in an oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with lemon wedge or tomato sauce.
Yield:
6 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: shrimp skillet
directions: Add rice to butter, onion, celery in skillet and saute until rice is golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then simmer uncovered 5 minutes.

title: veal pennsylvania
directions: Coat veal with flour.
In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add veal; cook about 2 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Add apples and pecans.
Cook and stir until apples are tender-crisp.
Add honey and brown sugar.
Cook and stir until warm.
Can serve on large croutons by cutting out white bread with large cookie cutter, sprinkle with salt and pepper and bake on cookie sheet 10 minutes at 350°.

title: becky's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening. Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Blend thoroughly and refrigerate or roll into biscuits.
Let rise slightly; bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Dough will keep up to 3 days in fridge.
Makes 8 fat biscuits.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Put all the ingredients except the sour cream in electric mixer container.
Mix on low speed 5 to 7 minutes until sugar has dissolved completely and emulsifed.
Add sour cream and mix 1 more minute.
Chill. Serve with whole berries for garnish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: horseradish ring
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Stir well.
Add cold water, salt and vinegar.
Stir.
Cool to jellied stage.
Stir in horseradish and whipped cream.
Pour into an oiled mold.
When thoroughly set, unmold.
Garnish with parsley leaflets.
Excellent with ham.

title: cheese breaded fish
directions: Beat eggs in separate bowl.
Take first 4 ingredients and place onto counter top lined with wax paper.
Take a rolling pin and roll ingredients into a crumblike mixture.
Cover all pieces of fish in egg mixture and then cover fish with crumb mixture to create batter taste.
Cook fish in skillet of oil for 6 minutes. Serves 3 to 4 people.
Very tasty!

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Mix all, except chips.
Let the mixture soak together for 10 minutes, then press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed potato chips, then bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pasta with tomato and basil
directions: Chop basil leaves.
Mince garlic.
Shred cheese.
Drop tomatoes in boiling water for about 10 seconds.
Peel and chop tomatoes. Mix tomatoes, basil, garlic and cheese with oil; let stand in covered bowl at room temperature for at least 3 hours.
Cook pasta and drain.
Add tomatoes to hot pasta and mix well.
Serve warm.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat the eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla together.
Place the bread pieces in a buttered baking dish (approximately 8 x 1 1/2-inches round).
Pour milk mixture over the bread.
Sprinkle on the raisins.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Wrap ribs in foil, bone side down.
Place on a cookie sheet; bake at 325° to 350° for 90 minutes.
Open foil; baste with barbecue sauce.
Cook, uncovered, an additional 30 minutes. Absolutely delicious!
And no clean up!

title: walnut pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one a a time, beating well after each.
At low speed, gradually beat in yogurt, milk and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients; beating until fluffy.
Scrape bowl as needed.
Stir in chopped walnuts.

title: cheese fondue bake
directions: Mix butter and mustard; then spread on one side of each slice of bread.
Cut bread into cubes.
Beat remaining ingredients with wire whisk until uniform.
Stir in bread cubes.
Pour into a well greased baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: my man's cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake	until
light and brown, 10 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in water until cooked.
Melt butter to liquid. Beat eggs.
Add all the ingredients together, stir it thoroughly. Bake at 350° in any baking pan until top is browned and casserole is lightly moist.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Combine all ingredients with the bananas being last.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing well.
Blend in egg.
Spread into bottom of crust.
Combine rest of ingredients; mix well.
Pour over cream cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together the sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour.
Stir in milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook in saucepan on medium heat, stirring continually.
Add butter and vanilla.
Fold in coconut. Pour in baked pie shell.

title: steak and rice casserole
directions: Trim bone and fat from steak and cut into 1-inch strips.
Brown steak in oil in skillet on top of stove.
Mix steak and all other ingredients in a covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: appetizer cheese bake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir in cheese and onion.
Spoon into a 1-quart souffle dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Serve immediately with crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: turkey chili
directions: In a large pan or Dutch oven, place oil, ground turkey, chili powder, salt and pepper.
On medium heat, stirring often, cook until meat has changed color.
Add tomato juice, picante sauce and pork and beans.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: shelva's sherbet punch
directions: Put ice cream and sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour juice and ginger ale over it and mix.
Serves 24.

title: zesty cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage and put in plastic bag; cook in microwave for approximately 25 minutes (if not fully cooked, put in for approximately 5 minutes more).
Let cool.
In microwave dish, prepare rice according to instructions on package; let cool.
Take sauce and put about 1 inch on bottom of lasagna dish.
Separate cabbage leaves, pulling off one at a time.
Take 1 loaf of cabbage.
Spread out and put on 1 large spoon of rice and 1 teaspoon of sour cream.
Flop in sides and roll.
Do this until all leaves are rolled and place them in the dish with sauce. Cover them with the rest of the sauce.
Sprinkle cheeses on top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot fruit juice
directions: Mix ingredients in large pot.
Heat on medium heat until mixture is hot (do not boil).
Serve hot.
Leftover juice can be refrigerated and reheated.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar.
Cream until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each.
Sift flour and baking powder; add a little at a time with milk.
Stir in flavoring.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Mix soup and sour cream and then mix in with chicken.
Crumble crackers over this and pour butter on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: welch fried cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add milk to eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add currants.
Mix and chill.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill a 9-inch pie plate 2/3 full of peeled and sliced apples. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of sugar, mixed with cinnamon.
In a small bowl, mix 1 cup of sugar, butter, flour, beaten egg and nuts.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.
Bake over a cookie sheet; might drip over the side.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add pineapple.
Let congeal a little then add pie filling and pecans.

title: italian sausage zucchini milano
directions: Crumble and saute sausage.
Remove sausage from skillet.
Keep tablespoon of drippings.
Add squash and onion, saute.
Add all other ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Put sausage on top.
Cover. Cook for 15 minutes.

title: "cool" cherry romanov
directions: Stir liqueur into pie filling.
Alternately spoon ice cream, whipped topping and cherry pie filling into dessert dishes or parfait glasses ending with whipped topping.
Garnish with a spoonful of cherry pie filling.
Any remaining whipped topping can be refrozen.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine raisins, fruit and water in saucepan.
Cook, uncovered, until water is evaporated and fruit is soft.
Set aside to cool.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, applesauce, sweetener, oil and vanilla.
Add nuts to fruit mixture.
Stir into dry ingredients and blend thoroughly. Pour into greased fluted tube pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: trifle
directions: Layer in clear glass bowl.

title: sandy's chili
directions: Brown meat, drain grease.
Add onion and cook till onion almost done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on medium to low heat until done.

title: pumpkin cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, flour, pumpkin, cinnamon, baking powder, salt and baking soda together. Pour into a greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 25 minutes.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Fill cupcakes 3/4 full of batter.
Mix egg, cream cheese, sugar and chocolate chips in middle of batter.
Sprinkle with nuts and sugar over top.
Bake as directed on cake box.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, rinse in cold water and drain in colander. Dice olives, pimiento and onion.
Toss in salad bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise to moisten.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut up cooked chicken.
Mix all ingredients together, except Miracle Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: spice bars
directions: Spread in pan.	Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pow - wows
directions: Mix bacon with chipped ham, chili sauce and relish.
Put a tablespoon of ham mixture on a sliced burger bun.
Top with a slice of cheese.
Close bun and wrap in foil.
Heat 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix together and bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Mix 3/4 cup powdered sugar with a little lemon juice and drizzle over bread.

title: bread pudding with apples and raisins
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and salt. In a round baking dish, add bread, apples and raisins.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
For a change, add the melted butter and sugar on bottom of dish.
Make bread pudding with apples and raisins as directed.
Cool.
Turn dish upside down over another dish.
The pudding will have a caramel type topping. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Enjoy.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Make pudding as directed on back of box; mix in pineapple. Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 10.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and well beaten egg.
Mash bananas with fork and add to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Pour into buttered loaf pan. Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour in 8 x 4 x 4-inch pan.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done. Add celery, onions and eggs. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar and sugar. Toss over potatoes. Garnish with paprika.

title: seven layer salad(taco flavored)
directions: Stir into drained meat the beans, and taco sauce.
Heat. Layer:
meat mixture, sharp grated Cheddar cheese, 1 cup sour cream, chopped onion, olives, tomatoes and green peppers.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch. Add lemon rind and juice. Stir. Add egg yolks and milk. Add butter. Cook over medium heat until thick. Cool. Fold in sour cream. Pour in baked pie crust. Top with meringue and bake at 400° for 10 or 12 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in saucepan milk, cocoa, sugar and butter.
Bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Have ready and stir in immediately peanut butter, quick cooking oats and vanilla.
Nuts are optional.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls and cool.

title: easy popsicles
directions: Mix juice together.
Cut hole in center of cover of 10 (1 ounce) cups with tops.
Fill cup with juice.
Place cover on top, then place craft stick or straw in hole securely.
Put into freezer until frozen.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together and press on a cookie sheet.
Chill overnight or put into freezer until firm.
Cut into 4-inch squares.
Roll in flour and brown on both sides in hot oil.
Place pieces in a baking dish.
Cover with 1 can mushroom soup and 1 can water mixed.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: plain pastry
directions: Mix well and form into a ball.
Let rest in refrigerator for about 20 minutes.
Cut ball in half and roll half just thin enough to be able to handle into a pie plate.
Place filling into pie plate with bottom crust in place.
Roll out top crust to same thickness as bottom and place on the pie.
Bake the pie according to the directions given with the filling.
Most 2-crust pies cook best when baked in a hot oven (450°) for about 10 minutes and the rest of the time in a moderate oven (350°).

title: jambalaya
directions: Chop up chicken breasts. Combine chicken with all ingredients except ham and rice. Bring to boil. Add ham and rice. Cover and simmer until rice is done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: stuffed manicotti shells
directions: Mix ingredients and stuff in manicotti shells which have been boiled for 10 minutes.
Pour spaghetti sauce over and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad #2
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine first 6 ingredients with 1 cup mayonnaise, sour cream and 1/2 cup milk.
Blend well.
Add macaroni and toss.
Refrigerate, covered, several hours.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into salad.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with the dried beef and horseradish. This is great on pumpernickel bread.

title: opera chicken
directions: Sprinkle half of stuffing over bottom of 10 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer rest in order given.
Blend soup and milk, pour over top.
Moisten remaining stuffing with melted butter and water, put on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until hot.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt margarine, then add sugar and eggs.
Cook together over low heat 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake 35 minutes at 345° in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Blend all the ingredients in a blender on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour in 9-inch greased pie plate.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Serve warm or cold.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Cut cucumbers into sticks.
Pour boiling water over and let stand overnight.
Next day, drain.
Pack solidly into jars.

title: caribbean fudge pie(kraft general foods, inc.)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate (melt in microwave or in double boiler), instant coffee and rum extract.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Decorate top with 1/2 cup walnut halves.
Bake in lower third of oven for 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream. Serves 8 to 10.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix all dressing ingredients and pour over lettuce.
Add croutons and stir once more.
Use Parmesan cheese before serving, if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour one loaf pan.
Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini lo-cal soup
directions: Saute the onion and zucchini in margarine until tender.
Add broth and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into blender, 1/3 at a time, and whip until smooth. Add milk, dill, salt and pepper.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Clean and cook whole green beans.
Place them in a sterile pint jar.
Boil the water, vinegar, sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt. Pour over beans and seal jar.
You may double recipe.

title: raspberry-rhubarb salad
directions: Heat rhubarb with sugar until soft.
Add Jell-O and stir.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice. Refrigerate until partially set. Add the rest of the ingredients and refrigerate again until completely set.

title: magic cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour cracker crumbs over margarine and spread.
Pour coconut on top and spread.
Pour chips on top and spread.
Pour nuts on top and spread.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over top and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting in squares.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except stuffing.
Sprinkle stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until it begins to bubble.

title: microwave vegetable soup
directions: Preparation time:
1 hour.
Use a 4-quart microwave pot with cover.
Cook ingredients on High for 20 minutes, stirring at 10 minutes.
Cook at 50% power for 25 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Taste softness of celery for doneness.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break up biscuits in a lightly greased or buttered dish.
Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 or 40 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Brown flour and onions in butter.
Add about 2 cups broth and simmer.
Use layer of chicken, then a layer of vegetables.
Pour 1/2 of the gravy over the chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Pull biscuits apart and place on top of cheese. Pour remainder gravy over the biscuits.
Bake until biscuits are browned, about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: easy meatballs for a group
directions: Fill slow cooker with meatballs. Combine sauce and jam. Pour over meatballs. Cover. Cook on low 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in jar and shake well. Store and keep indefinitely.
Good on chicken, beef and pork.

title: turkey and stuffing bake
directions: Combine butter and water; stir until butter melts.
Pour over seasoned stuffing crumbs; toss lightly.
Stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon stuffing mixture into a 9-inch shallow baking dish (1 1/2-quart) or pie plate.
Press stuffing across bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell.
Mix condensed celery soup, milk, turkey and peas together, then spoon into prepared baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: herbed seasoning blend
directions: Mix well and spoon into shaker.
Makes 1/3 cup.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine in a Dutch oven until tender.
Add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk, stirring until mixture boils.
Stir in corn and next 3 ingredients.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into bowls; sprinkle with paprika.
Yield:
3 servings.

title: pumpkin-nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until desired color (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).

title: easy bread
directions: Combine shortening and boiling water in bowl, stirring until shortening is melted.
Stir in salt and sugar.
Let stand and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in very warm water and add to shortening mixture.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour to make soft dough.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Simmer chicken until cooked.
Season if desired.
Reserve water that chicken simmered in for sauce.
Remove bones and cut into small strips or cubes.
Allow 1 ounce of chicken per enchilada. Grate cheese.
Allow 1/2 ounce cheese per enchilada.
Cut whole chilies into very thin strips and chop a little for garnish on top. Combine soup, broth (2 soup can measures), and seasonings in a saucepan.
Thicken with the cornstarch.
Soften tortillas in the sauce.
Remove tortillas from the sauce and fill each with 1 ounce of chicken, 1/2 ounce of cheese and 1 to 2 strips of green chilies. If desired, add 1 tablespoon of sauce and then roll.
Make sure the tortilla is soft enough or it will crack when rolling.
When pan is full, garnish with chopped chilies and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese is melted and toasty on top. Serves 8.

title: rev.  vriesen's potato pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients, drop on hot greased griddle and fry until golden brown.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix and cook, stirring constantly over medium heat until thick.
Put in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell with lattice top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400° or until done.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas until lightly fried, not crisp, in oil and dry, using paper towels. In a separate container, put cheese. Set aside. Mix together remaining ingredients in another large mixing bowl. Separately fill each tortilla with a small amount of "mix" and a small amount of grated cheese. Place "bed-fellow" style in a large baking dish. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and set aside.
Saute meat, onion and pepper; drain.
Add tomatoes, paste, sugar, oregano and garlic; set aside.
Combine spaghetti, margarine, Parmesan and eggs. Press in 10-inch pie plate.
Spread with cottage cheese.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy. Gradually add whipped topping and powdered sugar and continue beating until smooth.
Spoon filling into prepared crusts.
Freeze at least 8 hours or overnight.
Garnish with chocolate shavings, if desired.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: potato festival bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Mash potatoes while hot, then cool. Add potato water, scalded and cooled milk, salt, sugar and melted shortening to potatoes. Add softened yeast, then stir in flour.
Mix thoroughly, using only enough flour to make a stiff, kneadable dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in lightly greased bowl. Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk. Punch down and let rise again for about 1 hour.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise in greased bread pans.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for about 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Turn bread out onto racks to cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.
Makes approximately 40 (3-inch) balls.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter and add sifted dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and apples.
Pour in a bottom oil and floured 9x12 pan.

title: crackerjack cookies
directions: Cream butter well and blend in sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together and mix in. Stir in oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut by hand.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Omit coconut if desired.

title: sponge candy
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and vinegar in saucepan.
Cover tightly; bring to a boil.
Uncover; place a candy thermometer in the pan. Without stirring, cook over medium heat to 300°.
Gradually lower heat as mixture thickens to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; quickly stir in the baking soda and vanilla.
Turn into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not spread; candy will spread itself.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs, 1 cup flour with baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Cut fruit and nuts. Sprinkle the other cup flour over fruit and nuts.
Pour batter over fruit and nuts.
Mix with hands.
Line pan with heavy brown paper (grocery bag works fine).
Put in cold oven and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake for 2 1/2 hours. Place pan of water under cake while cooking.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, water, onion, salts, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoons into balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased baking dish 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over meatballs.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake 45 minutes.
Uncover, bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Frosting:
Grate peel and squeeze juice from lemon; mix confectioners sugar and add juice.

title: never fail peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread.
Then add peanuts and stir continually.
After peanuts are added, cook until it turns a light yellow.
Remove from heat.
Add soda, salt and butter.
Spread thin on buttered cookie sheet.
Break into pieces.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Cut four thin lemon slices; squeeze 2 teaspoons juice from remaining lemon.
Set aside.
In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove; set aside.
Spoon off fat. In skillet, combine soup, milk, reserved lemon juice and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet; top with lemon slices. Cover; cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring often.
Garnish with fresh thyme if desired.

title: cripple creek chicken
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine in small skillet; add paprika.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Roll in onion mixture.
Arrange in 11 x 15-inch casserole.
Spoon remaining onion mixture over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Stir in all ingredients except milk until moist and smooth, then add milk.
On medium heat, cook until thick and boiling.
In large bowl, put in alternating layers of vanilla wafers and bananas and pudding.

title: six-layer, one-dish dinner
directions: Layer potatoes, celery, ground hamburg steak, green pepper, onions and tomatoes.
Sprinkle on each layer separately:
2 teaspoons of salt and 1 teaspoon pepper.
Dot with butter.
Cover. Bake for 2 hours in moderate oven at 350°.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake crust at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.
Let cool and crumble into 9 inch x 13 inch dish. Save some to sprinkle on top.

title: corn dog mix
directions: Mix well; dip hot dogs in batter and deep fry.
This is enough for 2 pounds of hot dogs.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Cook celery and pepper in chicken broth.
Put noodles and all other ingredients in pan.
Add some grated cheese on top.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Icing: Bring sugar and water to a boil. Continue
boiling until mixture spins a thread and remove from heat. Beat egg whites while sugar mixture cooks. Egg whites
will form a peak. Add vanilla and heated sugar mixture to egg whites. Mix well.
